INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434001, 'Sometimes it''s hard to be a woman giving all your love to just one man.', 69107, 0), (434002, 'Stand by your man. Give him two arms to cling to and something warm to come to.', 69107, 0), (434003, 'Love is... never asking for more than you are prepared to give.', 69108, 0), (434004, 'If you''ve got love you''ve got life, if you can love you can live.', 69108, 0), (434005, 'My children are the reason I laugh, smile and want to get up every morning.', 69109, 0), (434006, 'At the end of the day, the most overwhelming key to a child''s success is the positive involvement of parents.', 69110, 0), (434007, 'Each day of our lives we make deposits in the memory banks of our children.', 1789, 0), (434008, 'The gain is not the having of children it is the discovery of love and how to be loving. ', 22501, 0), (434009, 'Don''t worry that children never listen to you worry that they are always watching you. ', 22, 0), (434010, 'Having a baby is a life-changer. It gives you a whole other perspective on why you wake up every day.', 69111, 0), (434011, 'I cannot think of any need in childhood as strong as the need for a father''s protection.', 555, 0), (434012, 'A baby is born with a need to be loved - and never outgrows it.', 27528, 0), (434013, 'Let parents bequeath to their children not riches, but the spirit of reverence.', 51, 0), (434014, 'Always kiss your children goodnight, even if they''re already asleep.', 63634, 0), (434015, 'To be a good father and mother requires that the parents defer many of their own needs and desires in favor of the needs of their children. As a consequence of this sacrifice, conscientious parents develop a nobility of character and learn to put into practice the selfless truths taught by the Savior Himself.', 9153, 0), (434016, 'Children are educated by what the grown-up is and not by his talk.', 28934, 0), (434017, 'When you hold your baby in your arms the first time, and you think of all the things you can say and do to influence him, it''s a tremendous responsibility. What you do with him can influence not only him, but everyone he meets and not for a day or a month or a year but for time and eternity.', 66690, 0), (434018, 'Every word, facial expression, gesture, or action on the part of a parent gives the child some message about self-worth. It is sad that so many parents don''t realize what messages they are sending.', 813, 0), (434019, 'I''m not a parenting expert. In fact, I''m not sure that I even believe in the idea of ''parenting experts.'' I''m an engaged, imperfect parent and a passionate researcher. I''m an experienced mapmaker and a stumbling traveler. Like many of you, parenting is by far my boldest and most daring adventure.', 247, 0), (434020, 'Children are not casual guests in our home. They have been loaned to us temporarily for the purpose of loving them and instilling a foundation of values on which their future lives will be built.', 22081, 0), (434021, 'The number of stressors has multiplied exponentially: traffic, money, success, work/life balance, the economy, the environment, parenting, family conflict, relationships, disease. As the nature of human life has become far more complicated, our ancient stress response hasn''t been able to keep up.', 69112, 0), (434022, 'Parents were invented to make children happy by giving them something to ignore.', 2247, 0), (434023, 'Even as kids reach adolescence, they need more than ever for us to watch over them. Adolescence is not about letting go. It''s about hanging on during a very bumpy ride.', 69113, 0), (434024, 'If you bungle raising your children, I don''t think whatever else you do matters very much.', 27555, 0), (434025, 'The child supplies the power but the parents have to do the steering.', 2463, 0), (434026, 'Abortion is defended today as a means of ensuring the equality and independence of women, and as a solution to the problems of single parenting, child abuse, and the feminization of poverty.', 28872, 0), (434027, 'There are times as a parent when you realize that your job is not to be the parent you always imagined you''d be, the parent you always wished you had. Your job is to be the parent your child needs, given the particulars of his or her own life and nature.', 21992, 0), (434028, 'The more people have studied different methods of bringing up children the more they have come to the conclusion that what good mothers and fathers instinctively feel like doing for their babies is the best after all.', 2463, 0), (434029, 'Every cliche about kids is true; they grow up so quickly, you blink and they''re gone, and you have to spend the time with them now. But that''s a joy.', 67563, 0), (434030, 'To me luxury is to be at home with my daughter, and the occasional massage doesn''t hurt.', 69114, 0), (434031, 'Autism is a neurological disorder. It''s not caused by bad parenting. It''s caused by, you know, abnormal development in the brain. The emotional circuits in the brain are abnormal. And there also are differences in the white matter, which is the brain''s computer cables that hook up the different brain departments.', 11095, 0), (434032, 'Childhood is a short season.', 4743, 0), (434033, 'Listen to the desires of your children. Encourage them and then give them the autonomy to make their own decision.', 1391, 0), (434034, 'Girls are the future mothers of our society, and it is important that we focus on their well-being.', 64289, 0), (434035, 'My mom and dad gave their kids the greatest gift of all - the gift of unconditional love. They cared deeply about who we would be, and much less about what we would do.', 52321, 0), (434036, 'Relationships are complicated no matter what style of parenting you choose.', 69115, 0), (434037, 'Childhood obesity is best tackled at home through improved parental involvement, increased physical exercise, better diet and restraint from eating.', 69116, 0), (434038, 'I think parenting these days is definitely different from when a lot of people grew up. As much blame as we give a lot of our kids for what they''re not doing... I also try to give them as much credit for dealing with things that we didn''t have to deal with. Bullying was one on one and face to face. Now it''s all over the Internet.', 69117, 0), (434039, 'Loving a child doesn''t mean giving in to all his whims; to love him is to bring out the best in him, to teach him to love what is difficult.', 44758, 0), (434040, 'It''s a great mistake, I think, to put children off with falsehoods and nonsense, when their growing powers of observation and discrimination excite in them a desire to know about things.', 69118, 0), (434041, 'You know, parenting is so personal. And we''re all afraid that we didn''t quite get it right. And it feels like the stakes are so high. By we - what if we made a mistake?', 3273, 0), (434042, 'Any kid will run any errand for you, if you ask at bedtime.', 62651, 0), (434043, 'Love is staying up all night with a sick child - or a healthy adult.', 5472, 0), (434044, 'Hugs can do great amounts of good - especially for children.', 68145, 0), (434045, 'Parents should not smoke in order to discourage their kids from smoking. A child is more likely to smoke when they have been raised in the environment of a smoker.', 69119, 0), (434046, 'I want to speak directly to the audience, to say, ''I''m like you - I''m frustrated, I''m not an expert, I don''t have a manual on parenting, I make mistakes, I''m selfish too.''', 68423, 0), (434047, 'Children should have enough freedom to be themselves - once they''ve learned the rules.', 1552, 0), (434048, 'We''ve had bad luck with our kids - they''ve all grown up.', 8661, 0), (434049, 'Nothing you do for children is ever wasted. They seem not to notice us, hovering, averting our eyes, and they seldom offer thanks, but what we do for them is never wasted.', 1205, 0), (434050, 'Parentage is a very important profession, but no test of fitness for it is ever imposed in the interest of the children.', 266, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434051, 'The relation between parents and children is essentially based on teaching.', 13906, 0), (434052, 'Mothers all want their sons to grow up to be president, but they don''t want them to become politicians in the process.', 1680, 0), (434053, 'Having children is like having a bowling alley installed in your brain.', 24366, 0), (434054, 'Mothers - especially single mothers - are heroic in their efforts to raise our nation''s children, but men must also take responsibility for their children and recognize the impact they have on their families'' well-being.', 69120, 0), (434055, 'Family involvement is a valuable thing and playing together actively can be the ''90s version of it. Instead of just watching, you can do it together... something we don''t spend enough time on. We can motivate and excite each other about fitness.', 68389, 0), (434056, 'Parenthood always comes as a shock. Postpartum blues? Postpartum panic is more like it. We set out to have a baby what we get is a total take-over of our lives. ', 22501, 0), (434057, 'The unconditional love for you child, it''s truly amazing.', 68192, 0), (434058, 'Everywhere, people are discovering that doing things more slowly often means doing them better and enjoying them more. It means living life instead of rushing through it. You can apply this to everything from food to parenting to work.', 30674, 0), (434059, 'Parenting is one of the hardest jobs on earth.', 883, 0), (434060, 'Parenting is not for sissies. You have to sacrifice and grow up.', 1860, 0), (434061, 'Parenting is the hardest thing I have ever done. I tried to find the balance between the strict, traditional Chinese way I was raised, which I think can be too harsh, and what I see as a tendency in the West to be too permissive and indulgent. If I could do it all again, I would, with some adjustments.', 3273, 0), (434062, 'My husband''s a pediatrician, so he and I talk about parenting all the time. You can''t raise children who have more shame resilience than you do.', 247, 0), (434063, 'Giving kids whatever they ask for is disastrous parenting. There''s no sense of something earned. I''m sorry, but when you''re 12, you don''t need a new cell phone every few months just because a new one comes out.', 7878, 0), (434064, 'The secret to success, to parenting, to life, is to not count up the cost. Don''t focus on all the steps it will take. Don''t stare into the abyss at the giant leap it will take. That view will keep you from taking the next small step.', 37774, 0), (434065, 'The parenting style that is good for grit is also the parenting style good for most other things: Be really, really demanding, and be very, very supportive.', 21372, 0), (434066, 'Modern parents want to nurture so skillfully that Mother Nature will gasp in admiration at the marvels their parenting produces from the soft clay of children.', 29034, 0), (434067, 'You learn that there''s no right way to do it, no wrong way to do it. It''s just what you feel comfortable with, to trust that, and don''t let anybody box you in to a certain style of parenting or make you feel a certain way about what your kids do.', 69121, 0), (434068, 'That''s my parenting style - ''Go watch the TV.'' I''m one of 11 children, and my mother''s parenting style was, ''There''s the TV. Go watch it. Mommy''s got 10 other people to take care of.''', 1450, 0), (434069, 'Nobody ever becomes an expert parent. But I think good parenting is about consistency. It''s about being there at big moments, but it''s also just the consistency of decision making. And it''s routine.', 67661, 0), (434070, 'Tell me how a person judges his or her self-esteem, and I will tell you how that person operates at work, in love, in sex, in parenting, in every important aspect of existence - and how high he or she is likely to rise. The reputation you have with yourself - your self-esteem - is the single most important factor for a fulfilling life.', 6169, 0), (434071, 'Few things are more satisfying than seeing your children have teenagers of their own.', 5026, 0), (434072, 'Education, like neurosis, begins at home.', 69122, 0), (434073, 'If you''re financially responsible, your children have a much better chance to grow up financially responsible.', 10090, 0), (434074, 'Many people think that discipline is the essence of parenting. But that isn''t parenting. Parenting is not telling your child what to do when he or she misbehaves. Parenting is providing the conditions in which a child can realize his or her full human potential.', 43700, 0), (434075, 'Kids are fat because of lack of parenting.', 17797, 0), (434076, 'Parenting involves two separate activities. You have to change your child in that you need to educate your child and instill moral values in them. But you also need to celebrate your child for who he or she is and make them feel really good.', 572, 0), (434077, 'At every step the child should be allowed to meet the real experience of life the thorns should never be plucked from his roses. ', 62381, 0), (434078, 'My worldview, my philosophy, my attitudes, my relationships, my parenting, my marriage - everything has been transformed by my relationship with Christ.', 9195, 0), (434079, 'I had no idea that mothering my own child would be so healing to my own sadness from my childhood.', 52036, 0), (434080, 'If we had paid no more attention to our plants than we have to our children, we would now be living in a jungle of weed.', 3603, 0), (434081, 'If you''re asking your kids to exercise, then you better do it, too. Practice what you preach.', 67828, 0), (434082, 'The uncertainty of parenting can bring up feelings in us that range from frustration to terror.', 247, 0), (434083, 'If I feel good about my parenting, I have no interest in judging other people''s choices. If I feel good about my body, I don''t go around making fun of other people''s weight or appearance. We''re hard on each other because we''re using each other as a launching pad out of our own perceived deficiency.', 247, 0), (434084, 'I came to parenting the way most of us do - knowing nothing and trying to learn everything.', 69115, 0), (434085, 'Leave part of the yard rough. Don''t manicure everything. Small children in particular love to turn over rocks and find bugs, and give them some space to do that. Take your child fishing. Take your child on hikes.', 13719, 0), (434086, 'Parenthood remains the greatest single preserve of the amateur.', 28611, 0), (434087, 'The family teaches us about the importance of knowledge, education, hard work and effort. It teaches us about enjoying ourselves, having fun, keeping fit and healthy.', 69123, 0), (434088, 'The well-being and welfare of children should always be our focus.', 67197, 0), (434089, 'We must return optimism to our parenting. To focus on the joys, not the hassles; the love, not the disappointments; the common sense, not the complexities.', 27683, 0), (434090, 'Of course, the ideal scenario for parenting is obviously two parents of a mature age.', 883, 0), (434091, 'Parenting now is a two-way relationship where you learn from each other.', 69124, 0), (434092, 'What lingers from the parent''s individual past, unresolved or incomplete, often becomes part of her or his irrational parenting.', 813, 0), (434093, 'I have a neuroscience background - that''s what my doctorate is in - and I was trained to study hormones of attachment, so I definitely feel my parenting is informed by that.', 69115, 0), (434094, 'If two very different people pool their DNA, they''ll create more genetic variety, and their young will come to the job of parenting with a wider array of skills.', 52746, 0), (434095, 'In truth, I am a single mother. But I don''t feel alone at all in parenting my daughter. Krishna has a whole other side of her family who loves her, too. And so Krishna is parented by me, but also by her grandmother and aunts and cousins and uncles and friends.', 24454, 0), (434096, 'Thing is, I went to a born-again Christian high school, was brought up in a traditional Mormon family where these ideas about parenting are of structure and sacrifice. To think outside of that idea of family and parenting that I''ve grown up with is tough but also very freeing.', 55738, 0), (434097, 'A mother who is really a mother is never free.', 143, 0), (434098, 'Children are our second chance to have a great parent-child relationship.', 12362, 0), (434099, 'I regret not having had more time with my kids when they were growing up.', 65679, 0), (434100, 'Do you want to be an artist and a writer, or a wife and a lover? With kids, your focus changes. I don''t want to go to PTA meetings.', 2108, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434101, 'That''s my ideal day, time with my boys.', 69125, 0), (434102, 'Success for me its to raise happy, healthy human beings.', 69126, 0), (434103, 'The Golden Rule of Parenting is do unto your children as you wish your parents had done unto you! ', 63656, 0), (434104, 'Don''t reward bad behavior. It is one of the first rules of parenting. During the financial cataclysm of 2008, we said it differently. When we bailed out banks that had created their own misfortune, we called it a ''moral hazard,'' because the bailout absolved the bank''s bad acts and created an incentive for it to make the same bad loans again.', 17581, 0), (434105, 'As a dad, you are the Vice President of the executive branch of parenting. It doesn''t matter what your personality is like, you will always be Al Gore to your wife''s Bill Clinton. She feels the pain and you are the annoying nerd telling them to turn off the lights.', 13056, 0), (434106, 'We put more emphasis on who can drive a car than on who can be a parent. And I think there ought to be mandatory parenting classes starting in high school, and you should have to have a license to be able to be a parent to explain that you don''t give alcohol to kids.', 69127, 0), (434107, 'Learning from wolves to interact with pet dogs makes about as much sense as, ''I want to improve my parenting - let''s see how the chimps do it!''', 69128, 0), (434108, 'I''ve decided the secret of parenting is benevolent neglect.', 69129, 0), (434109, 'Sleeping is one of the more private aspects of parenting; it happens in a quiet room, whereas eating is a more public aspect of parenting. Other people can see it and compare it to what their kids eat.', 50328, 0), (434110, 'Happiness is not always through success. Equally, the constant pursuit of success is sure unhappiness. But we have to find the balance. My own thoughts are that parenting is very personal. And we all feel enormous insecurity about parenting. What are they going to think of us 20 years down the line?', 3273, 0), (434111, 'To me, Slow parenting is about bringing balance into the home. Children need to strive and struggle and stretch themselves, but that does not mean childhood should be a race. Slow parents give their children plenty of time and space to explore the world on their own terms.', 30674, 0), (434112, 'My parents were definitely on the incentive side of parenting. Like, they told me that my father had learned to read when he was three. So, of course, I thought I had to, too.', 10320, 0), (434113, 'Don''t judge other people. For example, if you want God''s anointing to be on you for parenting, you need to be careful not to criticize other parents.', 1206, 0), (434114, 'I think Lincoln had a unique parenting style. He let his kids run free and wild.', 5194, 0), (434115, 'Most moms and dads, they want to be good moms and dads. But it''s an incredibly hard job when you are stressed out, when you are poor, when your life is in chaos. And giving them some of the tools to be better parents, to whittle away at that parenting gap, gives those kids a much better starting point in life.', 47722, 0), (434116, 'I sort of feel like people are not that honest about their own parenting. Take any teenage household tell me there is not yelling and conflict. ', 3273, 0), (434117, 'Tiger parenting is all about raising independent, creative, courageous kids. In America today, there''s a dangerous tendency to romanticize creativity in a way that may undermine it.', 3273, 0), (434118, 'I believe that at least 70 percent of parenting goes to the mother. In our house, I''m the one who knows about all the school stuff, helps with the homework, organizes the play dates, and remembers the birthday parties.', 18113, 0), (434119, 'The basic idea that incentives can be used to motivate behavior is a powerful one. It works for employees, and it has a clear place in parenting, as anyone who has tried to potty-train a recalcitrant toddler with sticker rewards knows.', 69130, 0), (434120, 'Parenting is the most important job on the planet next to keeping Gary Busey off the nation''s highways.', 28316, 0), (434121, 'Parenting is not giving your child everything they want. Parenting is not being your child''s friend. Parenting is about preparing your child to be a useful and respectful person in society.', 69131, 0), (434122, 'Children live in the only successful Marxist state ever created: the family. ''From each according to his ability, to each according to his need'' is the family''s practice as well as its theory. Even with today''s scattershot patterns of marriage and parenting, a family is collectivist to a more than North Korean degree.', 10731, 0), (434123, 'Most American children suffer too much mother and too little father.', 1739, 0), (434124, 'My childhood should have taught me lessons for my own fatherhood, but it didn''t because parenting can only be learned by people who have no children.', 2059, 0), (434125, 'My son was five months old, and I built a makeshift studio in my living room so that I could do the attachment parenting approach and write the record at the same time. That was fortuitous, that we could build that in the house.', 21687, 0), (434126, 'I think parenting is very different now. We''re totally governed by our children!', 69023, 0), (434127, 'Parenting is not for everybody. It changes your life. Especially when they''re little.', 1549, 0), (434128, 'Gerard and I pretty much share all parenting responsibilities, although I''m definitely the disciplinarian.', 67847, 0), (434129, 'From politics to parenting, Christians have something to say.', 69132, 0), (434130, 'Ironically, parenting is a shame and judgment minefield precisely because most of us are wading through uncertainty and self-doubt when it comes to raising our children.', 247, 0), (434131, 'Growth doesn''t hurt. This is what I''ve learned. In the end, it doesn''t hurt. It hurts while it''s happening. But in the end, you know, for life, for parenting, and for the arts, it''s not a bad - not a bad thing to try for.', 68913, 0), (434132, 'The children who are ''our future'' will inherit a world created not just by parental devotion but by the sort of zealous, focused endeavors that can preclude good parenting.', 68175, 0), (434133, 'I barely have time for my own children. To adopt more children and not have time for them, that would be poor parenting on my part.', 47442, 0), (434134, 'Parenting isn''t just parenting your own child.', 1870, 0), (434135, 'Whatever needed to be done, I need to know how to do it just as well as my wife. You know, for us to be able to really balance the parenting. It was very humbling, and it was also, um - terrifying. Because, you know, giving a baby a bath for the first time is one of the scariest things you can do on this whole earth.', 69133, 0), (434136, 'I''ve been lucky enough to live through all the things that are supposed to give meaning to our lives, like parenting, grandparenting, art, celebrity. All these things you expect meaning to come from, and sometimes it comes when you''re not expecting it.', 15994, 0), (434137, 'Becoming a father, I think it inevitably changes your perspective of life. I don''t get nearly enough sleep. And the simplest things in life are completely satisfying. I find you don''t have to do as much, like you don''t go on as many outings.', 43985, 0), (434138, 'I love to read books that focus on parenting topics because there are so many different ways to do things. I find these books offer a lot of great opinions on many different subjects.', 67014, 0), (434139, 'I am always trying to evolve, so I like to read parenting books and things like that.', 67014, 0), (434140, 'We learn much of parenting from our own parents. My love for my father deepened profoundly when he was kind, patient, and understanding.', 9153, 0), (434141, 'The interesting thing about being a mother is that everyone wants pets, but no one but me cleans the kitty litter.', 5983, 0), (434142, 'My parents were divorced when I was a young teenager, and I was raised by a single mother after that. So, I understand the difficulties that families have. I understand single parenting.', 66573, 0), (434143, 'As a housewife, I feel that if the kids are still alive when my husband gets home from work, then hey, I''ve done my job.', 18054, 0), (434144, 'I''m torn about late parenting. I believe people should spend their twenties living and having fun and not having any regrets later. I also think people in their thirties generally make better parents but so many of my friends are having trouble - myself included - as fathers get older.', 69134, 0), (434145, 'My work makes me a better mom. It gives me a little door to step out of my parenting and bring the excitement from my day back home.', 63466, 0), (434146, 'My guess is that good and bad parenting is spread fairly evenly across different social groups. But can you imagine Tony Blair lecturing the middle class on how to bring up their children? He is far more comfortable as a latter-day exponent of the Poor Law mentality.', 67041, 0), (434147, 'In my experience (I am the lone father of an eight-year-old boy who lost his mother when he was one year old), parenting is the most difficult of all jobs: forget your chief executives, editors, prime ministers and the like - parenting is far more challenging.', 67041, 0), (434148, 'My grandmother was a kind of Scarsdale, New York, society woman, best known in her day as the author of the 1959 book ''Growing Your Own Way: An Informal Guide for Teen-Agers'' - this despite being a person whose parenting style made Joan Crawford''s wire hangers look like pool noodles.', 1436, 0), (434149, 'Ah, the power of two. There''s nothing quite like it. Especially when it comes to paying utility bills, parenting, cooking elaborate meals, purchasing a grown-up bed, jumping rope and lifting heavy machinery. The world favours pairs. Who wants to waste the wood building an ark for singletons?', 1436, 0), (434150, 'A picture excites the love of parenting that comes through meditation on a child.', 69135, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434151, 'Parenthood and family come first for me, and when I''m not working I''m cool with the Teletubbies.', 69136, 0), (434152, 'Very often when you see families it''s all perfect and neat, and parenting isn''t like that. You do have constant negotiations. Things are ever developing and ever changing, and you constantly have to evaluate how you deal with your kids.', 69136, 0), (434153, 'There''s this constant guilt that comes with parenting. You always feel like you''re never enough. If you''re confident in your parenting, you probably suck at it.', 13031, 0), (434154, '''Kramer vs. Kramer'' is one of my favorite films, where you have a story that really juxtaposes a lot of ideas that we have about family and about parenting.', 69137, 0), (434155, 'The parenting bit is much harder than the acting bit. You just never know what to do.', 45886, 0), (434156, 'Kids are a great analogy. You want your kids to grow up, and you don''t want your kids to grow up. You want your kids to become independent of you, but it''s also a parent''s worst nightmare: That they won''t need you. It''s like the real tragedy of parenting.', 90, 0), (434157, 'While not impossible, it is especially challenging for teenage parents to develop bonds with their children. A high percent of them were themselves children of teenage parents and have never experienced appropriate parenting.', 64250, 0), (434158, 'I think a dad has to make his daughter feel that he''s genuinely interested in what she''s going through.', 68271, 0), (434159, 'I think that good parenting should allow children to be children. That naivety and slightly open way of looking at the world is very valuable.', 69138, 0), (434160, 'The Internet is just bringing all kinds of information into the home. There''s just a lot of distraction, a lot of competition for the parent''s voice to resonate in the children''s ears.', 68937, 0), (434161, 'Having children with someone is the real bond.', 69139, 0), (434162, 'My parenting heroes are the Obamas! They''ve been married for so long, and it looks like they''re having fun, and their kids are down to earth, well-adjusted, and smart. They seem to have a strong family unit that I would like to emulate in my life.', 69131, 0), (434163, 'Today''s new age parenting guarantees you''ll hear children screaming, whining, and begging for items and attention in an airplane, store or any other public place.', 69131, 0), (434164, 'The government cannot overcome bad parenting. What our leaders can do is publicly condemn irresponsible parental behavior in vivid terms.', 47187, 0), (434165, 'There''s no handbook for parenting. So you walk a very fine line as a parent because you are civilizing these raw things. They will tip the coffee over and finger-paint on the table. At some point, you have to say, ''We''re gonna have to clean that up because you don''t paint with coffee on a table.''', 3625, 0), (434166, 'Parenting is an impossible job at any age.', 12392, 0), (434167, 'In Los Angeles, parenting is a competitive sport. From Beverly Hills baby boutiques to kids'' yoga classes, L.A. fuses high style, industrial-strength materialism, and parental outsourcing into our own unique version of child-rearing.', 69140, 0), (434168, 'No fathers or mothers think their own children ugly.', 62284, 0), (434169, 'No, I''ve never wanted kids. But I do read about parenting a lot.', 15776, 0), (434170, 'Parenting girls makes you quite gender-conscious - it''s almost impossible to fight the power of pink. It''s not such a terrible thing to want to be a princess when you''re five, but it would be nice if there were some other options.', 69141, 0), (434171, 'I''m worried about parents who aren''t parenting.', 11962, 0), (434172, 'Women are individuals in parenting, and why not?', 405, 0), (434173, 'I''m trying to break any chain of negative parenting that I might have survived.', 18483, 0), (434174, 'I want to have children, but my friends scare me. One of my friends told me she was in labor for 36 hours. I don''t even want to do anything that feels good for 36 hours.', 2210, 0), (434175, 'What parent has it easy? I just never make the difficulty of it an obstacle. I just do it.', 67063, 0), (434176, 'I would love to have kids one day. In fact, I''m pretty good with them. I grew up with five half-siblings, the youngest of whom is 11 years younger than me, so I think I learned some pretty cool parenting skills quite early on in life.', 68455, 0), (434177, 'Asian American success is often presented as something of a horror - robotic, unfeeling machines psychotically hellbent on excelling, products of abusive tiger parenting who care only about test scores and perfection, driven to succeed without even knowing why.', 24396, 0), (434178, 'No matter how much time you spend reading books or following your intuition, you''re gonna screw it up. Fifty times. You can''t do parenting right.', 68949, 0), (434179, 'Loving and parenting a dog as a single parent can create all sorts of new and unusual problems, but also new sources of joy.', 67565, 0), (434180, 'My dad was not super-intentional in his parenting. He was very self-absorbed. I won''t say mean or selfish per se, but very self-absorbed. I think he was just thinking out loud.', 21372, 0), (434181, 'Parenting is tough.', 67448, 0), (434182, 'Around a third of parents still worry that they will look like a bad mother or father if their child has a mental health problem. Parenting is hard enough without letting prejudices stop us from asking for the help we need for ourselves and our children.', 67448, 0), (434183, 'I love, love, love being an actor - it''s still the hardest and scariest thing I do, outside of parenting. But I''ve always been someone who likes a busy day.', 4816, 0), (434184, 'I''m afraid the parenting advice to come out of developmental psychology is very boring: pay attention to your kids and love them.', 20620, 0), (434185, 'The science can tell you that the thousands of pseudo-scientific parenting books out there - not to mention the ''Baby Einstein'' DVDs and the flash cards and the brain-boosting toys - won''t do a thing to make your baby smarter. That''s largely because babies are already as smart as they can be smarter than we are in some ways. ', 20620, 0), (434186, 'I would like to do another piece of fiction dealing with a number of issues: Lesbian parenting, the 1960''s, and interracial relationships in the Lesbian and Gay community.', 897, 0), (434187, 'The thing about parenting rules is there aren''t any. That''s what makes it so difficult.', 7878, 0), (434188, 'Mama and Daddy King represent the best in manhood and womanhood, the best in a marriage, the kind of people we are trying to become.', 16899, 0), (434189, 'We had a kid. The kid was awesome. She didn''t fall asleep easily. We complained about it. We got frustrated. But we didn''t look for an out. We just accepted that this was part of parenting.', 50328, 0), (434190, 'When it comes right down to it, developing a critical sensibility about parenting isn''t really about disapproval; it''s about honing your own sensibilities, figuring out how you want to parent.', 50328, 0), (434191, 'It''s hilarious to me that by writing an obscene fake children''s book I am mistaken for a parenting expert.', 50328, 0), (434192, 'I do not think there was anything abusive in my house. Yet, I stand by a lot of my critiques of Western parenting. I think there''s a lot of questions about how you instill true self-esteem.', 3273, 0), (434193, 'To be honest, I know that a lot of Asian parents are secretly shocked and horrified by many aspects of Western parenting.', 3273, 0), (434194, 'I think there are many ways to raise great kids. From what I can tell, Ayelet Waldman''s kids are interesting, strong, and happy, and if that''s the case, that''s good parenting.', 3273, 0), (434195, 'We go into parenting, and we discover that we don''t have the answers. We are at a loss.', 3977, 0), (434196, 'Parenting is no sport for perfectionists.', 572, 0), (434197, 'The most rewarding aspect of parenting is seeing my children be authentic. The most rewarding thing for me is to see them do anything that they''re proud of.', 47322, 0), (434198, 'The challenging part of parenting for me is to make sure that an individual person is an individual and not some sort of cookie-cutter version of me. At the same time, I want to make sure that I impart my sense of the world as an adult.', 47322, 0), (434199, 'Attachment parenting demands not just certain actions you take with your baby but also certain emotional states to accompany those actions.', 28478, 0), (434200, 'I don''t think my father considered allowing a teenager to follow his dreams was necessarily good parenting, or even parenting. I think he thought I was a teenager with teenage impulses. I''m pretty sure he knew that if he just let me follow those impulses, it would wind up being very expensive and perhaps even life-endangering.', 33965, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434201, 'Parenting is difficult under any circumstances, and in my father''s view, to raise a morally upright and honest child, you sometimes have to lie to him.', 33965, 0), (434202, 'I think I''m going to have to live vicariously through my daughter''s rebellion because I certainly never did go through adolescence.', 65022, 0), (434203, 'I thought that once we were out of the baby stage, parenting would be a breeze.', 900, 0), (434204, 'I''m not a parent, but it seems to me the nature of parenting is contingent, full of unexpected challenges - which is one of the wonderful and amazing things about it.', 69142, 0), (434205, 'Parenting is meant to be just a natural part of life. You just think you know how to do it but, of course, it''s much more complicated than that.', 69143, 0), (434206, 'As soon as you become a parent, everyone gives you their parenting advice. It''s like an onslaught of information about how other people do it.', 69143, 0), (434207, 'It''s a huge change for your body. You don''t even want to look in the mirror after you''ve had a baby, because your stomach is just hanging there like a Shar-Pei.', 18113, 0), (434208, 'Studies show that children best flourish when one mom and one dad are there to raise them.', 66633, 0), (434209, 'I feel very blessed to have two wonderful, healthy children who keep me completely grounded, sane and throw up on my shoes just before I go to an awards show just so I know to keep it real.', 61441, 0), (434210, 'Society should see parenting as a public health issue and help parents to bring their children up feeling loved. We have birthing classes, but no parenting classes. The latter is desperately needed if we are to avoid self-destruction.', 64551, 0), (434211, 'I''ve become sort of an accidental advocate for attachment parenting, which is a style of parenting that... basically, the way mammals parent and the way people have parented for pretty much all of human history except the last 200 years or so.', 69115, 0), (434212, 'Attachment parenting is not a passive parenting style.', 69115, 0), (434213, 'Indeed - judicious, consistent parenting is a dream of mine. No judgements, learning space and listening carefully are my goals.', 689, 0), (434214, 'I hope to find the roles that are age appropriate but not yearning to be younger, or parenting ad nauseam.', 68968, 0), (434215, 'It''s hard enough to work and raise a family when your kids are all healthy and relatively normal, but when you add on some kind of disability or disease, it can just be such a burden.', 69144, 0), (434216, 'I don''t think children''s inner feelings have changed. They still want a mother and father in the very same house they want places to play. ', 2288, 0), (434217, 'My approach to parenting is that everything is open - everything. I''m not very good at covert, or subtle, and I''ve had to learn timing. I do blunder in a bit.', 18101, 0), (434218, 'I have a shallow understanding of what it means to be alive, and I know certain things about parenting and being a wife and doing the school run. I know little bits, but I''m really a paddler on a beach.', 69145, 0), (434219, 'Being a chef isn''t the ideal career to intersect with parenting, but I try to be in my kids'' lives as much as possible.', 69146, 0), (434220, 'I adore my family. I don''t love their politics. I think they''re wonderful parents. They were dreadful at parenting.', 9587, 0), (434221, 'Should kids check phones at dinner? I don''t know. To me, that''s a parenting choice.', 45284, 0), (434222, 'I think we''ve moved to thinking of parenting and pregnancy as something in which you should lose yourself.', 69130, 0), (434223, 'I feel sure that unborn babies pick their parents.', 49634, 0), (434224, 'I told my kids when they were little, ''Look, kids, your mother and I are screwing you up somehow. We don''t understand how, or we wouldn''t do it. But we''re parents. So somehow we''re damaging you, and I want you to know that early. So just ignore me when I go to that part of my parenting.''', 2045, 0), (434225, 'Here''s a confession: I hate parenting books. I hate the ones that are earnest and repetitive.', 4516, 0), (434226, 'I set out to write an anti-parenting parenting book.', 4516, 0), (434227, 'We''re living in a time when parenting is not at all mirroring the way I was parented. For me, I just followed my parents around on their errands; when they were busy on the phone, I was quiet. It''s a different kettle of fish these days: They run the house, and you listen to their music, and you go to their appointments.', 69147, 0), (434228, 'The truth about parenting is that the reality of our lives needs to be enough.', 18056, 0), (434229, 'I think that the ideal of parenting can make people unhappy. It''s that this lie that they''re being told by society that parenting is one thing - and when parenting is something completely different - that''s what makes them unhappy.', 18056, 0), (434230, 'How pleasant it is for a father to sit at his child''s board. It is like an aged man reclining under the shadow of an oak which he has planted.', 972, 0), (434231, 'Whether I''m running, working, relating, parenting, learning - whatever I''m doing, I want to surround myself with people who push me.', 12208, 0), (434232, 'I''m not the first to admit that raising a child in Park Slope, Brooklyn, can bear an embarrassing resemblance to the TV show ''Portlandia.'' My wife and I try to have some ironic distance from the culture of organic, chemical-free parenting, but we''re often participants.', 69148, 0), (434233, 'I realize that of all people, I am no expert on parenting or marriage.', 69149, 0), (434234, 'My parenting style is probably like that of my parents, because you do how you learn. My mother was very nurturing and loving, but very stern. She was a disciplinary. My dad was also very loving.', 69150, 0), (434235, 'Slow parents understand that childrearing should not be a cross between a competitive sport and product-development. It is not a project it''s a journey. Slow parenting is about giving kids lots of love and attention with no conditions attached. ', 30674, 0), (434236, 'Smaller families mean we have more time and money to lavish on each child. Parents are more anxious because small families give them less experience of parenting and put their genetic eggs in fewer baskets.', 30674, 0), (434237, 'In my career as a writer, I preferred to avoid current events: I wrote young adult novels and book reviews and lifestyle journalism about health and parenting and other such evergreens.', 69151, 0), (434238, 'I take my children everywhere, but they always find their way back home.', 3158, 0), (434239, 'Never raise your hand to your children - it leaves your midsection unprotected.', 3158, 0), (434240, 'I take parenting incredibly seriously. I want to be there for my kids and help them navigate the world, and develop skills, emotional intelligence, to enjoy life, and I''m lucky to be able to do that and have two healthy, normal boys.', 68513, 0), (434241, 'The way I was parented did affect my parenting - probably in the reverse. My dad was pretty strict, and the next generation probably wants to be less strict.', 68389, 0), (434242, 'For decades, parents were told by so-called parenting ''experts'' that offspring would be best raised on the belief each is special and entitled to all life has to offer.', 43433, 0), (434243, 'Most people who have grown up introverted in this very extroverted culture of ours have had painful experiences of feeling like they are out of step with what''s expected of them. Parenting can pose unique challenges for introverted parents, who fear that their own painful experiences will be repeated in their children''s lives.', 1982, 0), (434244, 'I grew up with no money. My kids will grow up with a lot of money and so it''s really important to me, and it will always be a part of my parenting, to keep them conscientious and connected socially to other people.', 69152, 0), (434245, 'We expect teachers to handle teenage pregnancy, substance abuse, and the failings of the family. Then we expect them to educate our children.', 69153, 0), (434246, 'I don''t claim to know everything about parenting, but I do know parents do their children a disservice by constantly sugarcoating their shortcomings to protect their feelings.', 69154, 0), (434247, 'So, you know, parenting is a very intimate and amazing experience and one of the best experiences of my life.', 69155, 0), (434248, 'Offering unequal leaves just reinforces the longstanding notion that parenting responsibilities aren''t equal, and that doesn''t help anyone.', 69156, 0), (434249, 'No work-family balance will ever fully take hold if the social conditions that might make it possible - men who are willing to share parenting and housework, communities that value work in the home as highly as work on the job, and policymakers and elected officials who are prepared to demand family-friendly reforms - remain out of reach.', 18332, 0), (434250, 'In response to our fast-food culture, a ''slow food'' movement appeared. Out of hurried parenthood, a move toward slow parenting could be growing. With vital government supports for state-of-the-art public child care and paid parental leave, maybe we would be ready to try slow love and marriage.', 18332, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434251, 'I have three daughters, so I can''t be as tough as I want to be. When you have kids - especially daughters - they know how to work you. They''re a lot smarter than we are, that''s for sure. But I''ll be more tough on their boyfriends.', 6465, 0), (434252, 'I can only speak for my husband and myself, but we don''t feel like we could do any of this parenting without our faith.', 69157, 0), (434253, 'Some have said that ''Frankenstein'' is a story of a bad parenting giving rise to a troubled child.', 69158, 0), (434254, 'There''s nothing to be gained, and much to be lost, in trying to bend every child to match a one-size-fits-all notion of what it means to be a boy or girl of a specific age. Better to set a few parameters and then go with the flow. Call it ''jazz parenting.''', 69159, 0), (434255, 'My father was a farmer and my mother was a farmer, but, my childhood was very good. I am very grateful for my childhood, because it was full of gladness and good humanity.', 69160, 0), (434256, 'There are 80 million moms in the United States. Forty million stay at home with their children.', 68032, 0), (434257, 'I learned that life is about the people around you and the people you give back to. That''s what parenting is: You''re not there for yourself you''re there for your offspring and everyone else around you. ', 61808, 0), (434258, 'Mom and Dad would stay in bed on Sunday morning, but the kids would have to go to church.', 1652, 0), (434259, 'You have to support your children to have a healthy relationship.', 69161, 0), (434260, 'I''m doing a lot of parenting work and acting as a spokesperson. I have a clothing line and a line of toys.', 69162, 0), (434261, 'If there is any truth to my parenting the dreamwork movement, it comes from the power of the press.', 41366, 0), (434262, 'We all, as parents, are laughing at ourselves and helicopter parenting and saying, ''This isn''t the way we were parented; we were allowed to run free.'' When I talk to my friends, we are all fascinated by what we are doing, but we can''t seem to stop ourselves.', 6066, 0), (434263, 'Being a father of three children and grandfather to nine, I do think that this thing called ''parenting'' is becoming increasingly difficult.', 69163, 0), (434264, 'Believe me, my children have more stamina than a power station.', 67664, 0), (434265, 'Becoming a mother has been the best thing ever for me. It''s become my life''s work. Not just parenting, but sharing information and encouraging other women to be receptive to the basic nature of motherhood.', 69164, 0), (434266, 'You can make sure your kids make their beds and hang up their clothes and put their dishes in the dishwasher when you''re the one calling the shots. So, parenting alone, for me anyway, I think is almost easier, being single.', 67194, 0), (434267, 'For me, conscious parenting is staying attuned to your child, being really open and in the moment. It means staying as present as possible in your own breath for the betterment of your whole family.', 69164, 0), (434268, 'Parenting is not just about you and your kid it''s also about whomever you''re parenting your child with. So there is a kind of ''awareness'' involved for everybody. It''s all about the way you interact with your child and participate in your child''s life. ', 69164, 0), (434269, 'Children that are raised in a home with a married mother and father consistently do better in every measure of well-being than their peers who come from divorced or step-parent, single-parent, cohabiting homes.', 67197, 0), (434270, 'In parenting, as in judging, the days are long, but the years are short.', 69165, 0), (434271, 'I come from a dysfunctional family, so my views of parents and parenting used to be highly mixed.', 2177, 0), (434272, 'Single parenting is sometimes just a case of sitting around by yourself in mild despair, not knowing what to do.', 4035, 0), (434273, 'I suppose it''s amazing how quick life goes by when you have children.', 63002, 0), (434274, 'Dad was a strict disciplinarian and would give us a wallop with a wooden spoon if we were out of order. But we really respected him - he didn''t try to be our best friend.', 68060, 0), (434275, 'I''m endlessly fascinated by parenting, marriage, my wife and the ins and outs of marriage.', 26833, 0), (434276, 'It''s really hard to figure out what they need to know. And that''s parenting, in general. It''s hard to figure out what would benefit your kids and what would just make them needlessly frightened.', 68601, 0), (434277, 'I''m a parent, especially when you''ve had the intense parenting the way I had. It''s all in the bank. It''s all in the great experience bank. Those are your secrets. That''s the stuff that makes your work rich, that''s what you dip into.', 69166, 0), (434278, 'Parents forgive their children least readily for the faults they themselves instilled in them.', 20540, 0), (434279, 'My father wasn''t really involved and my mom is the light in my life.', 69167, 0), (434280, 'There''s really no point in having children if you''re not going to be home enough to father them.', 67222, 0), (434281, 'For me, Twitter works best as a way of taking pictures of being stuck in traffic on the Brooklyn Bridge. If people really want to read really funny quips about life, parenting, and pop culture, then by all means read Michael Ian Black''s tweets.', 68620, 0), (434282, 'When I was a kid, my mother''s parenting style teetered between benign neglect and intense bouts of violence.', 6012, 0), (434283, 'It''s difficult to keep that perspective, I think, as a parent: to know your boundaries as to what''s good parenting or just projecting your own expectations on your kids. That''s the hardest.', 67222, 0), (434284, 'Fathers and mothers have lost the idea that the highest aspiration they might have for their children is for them to be wise... specialized competence and success are all that they can imagine.', 2791, 0), (434285, 'I wasn''t very good about juggling family and my career. I was interested in who was coming to the children''s birthday party, what my son was writing. I was thinking about Legos.', 69168, 0), (434286, 'We criticize mothers for closeness. We criticize fathers for distance. How many of us have expected less from our fathers and appreciated what they gave us more? How many of us always let them off the hook?', 194, 0), (434287, 'Parenting classes should be mandatory, whether you are adopting or not, and would include an evaluation of your current physical, mental and financial state as well as how ready you are to take on the rigors of parenthood. Our children are our most precious natural resource, and there is absolutely no other way to parent but to put them first.', 69127, 0), (434288, 'As a rule, I try to steer clear of opinions pertaining to your parenting. I assume you''re doing the best you can, and God bless.', 13185, 0), (434289, 'A parentologist is a person who writes a book about parenting that is very clear about answers to, ''How am I supposed to raise my child?'' Some of these well-intentioned people may be a bit too sure-footed on the sometimes slippery slope of parenting.', 69169, 0), (434290, 'No one knows his true character until he has run out of gas, purchased something on the installment plan and raised an adolescent.', 63122, 0), (434291, 'Parents learn a lot from their children about coping with life.', 3292, 0), (434292, 'It is a sad commentary of our times when our young must seek advice and counsel from ''Dear Abby'' instead of going to Mom and Dad.', 69170, 0), (434293, 'Edith Vonnegut behaved like a guest in her children''s lives. To her way of thinking, parenting came under the general heading of household tasks, which, as a wealthy woman, she could pay others to do.', 69171, 0), (434294, 'I had three children while doing a show, as demanding as ''Good Morning America,'' so this is - you know, it''s almost like I''m less daunted about motherhood, and parenting at this point in time. And I think I''m just much more fit and healthy than I was 20-years-ago.', 370, 0), (434295, 'My father once said about being a parent that it is the only thing you do that requires a very long period of learning, and at about the time that you are becoming competent, you don''t need the skills anymore. Notwithstanding this modest assessment of their parenting skills, they were wonderful parents.', 69172, 0), (434296, 'Family life was wonderful. The streets were bleak. The playgrounds were bleak. But home was always warm. My mother and father had a great relationship. I always felt ''safe'' there.', 1587, 0), (434297, 'Parenting a pre-teen is quite something.', 69173, 0), (434298, 'I''m hosting weekend retreats all over America. It is like a 24-hour slumber party for moms. We laugh, eat, play games, get massages, win prizes, talk about parenting and even cry a bit.', 69174, 0), (434299, 'My kids love it. I thought I was the coolest dad in the world when I got to be in a Bond film, but ''Harry Potter'', too? Well, I think I qualify for a medal for exceptional parenting or something, don''t you?', 69175, 0), (434300, 'I have this blanket thing about giving parenting advice to parents, and that''s: ''Don''t take other people''s advice on parenting.''', 69176, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434301, 'Some men don''t want to be responsible fathers. It''s easier to say ''Let''s just turn the kids over to the state.'' Women end up bearing the entire load, raising kids alone without a husband to share the parenting.', 69177, 0), (434302, 'My mother was the influence in my life. She was strong she had great faith in the ultimate triumph of justice and hard work. She believed passionately in education. ', 68178, 0), (434303, 'I''d just as soon stay home and raise babies.', 69178, 0), (434304, 'I think letting babies cry it out is barbaric. Why would parenting stop when it''s dark outside? You can''t expect a baby to know that he''s supposed to sleep just because we want to go to bed.', 69179, 0), (434305, 'I''m not a parenting expert by any means, but I''ve been interviewing and writing about kids for almost 20 years.', 58004, 0), (434306, 'We are apt to forget that children watch examples better than they listen to preaching.', 54830, 0), (434307, 'I get whatever placidity I have from my father. But my mother taught me how to take it on the chin.', 69180, 0), (434308, 'I really like ''Shameless'' because it brings up important issues, but we get to talk and laugh and look at something that''s really important that''s a problem, like alcoholism and bad parenting. It''s done in a funny, smart way.', 69036, 0), (434309, 'A lot of kids have parents who say, ''Music is hard; maybe you should come up with a Plan B.'' Whenever I hear that kind of ''advice,'' I think it''s bad parenting. I was lucky to have a parent who assured me it was a possibility to pursue music.', 69181, 0), (434310, 'Parents are key when it comes to keeping kids off drugs. Good parenting is the best anti-drug we have.', 68689, 0), (434311, 'Being a mother of two myself - and two small girls - I think that single parenting is hard.', 69182, 0), (434312, 'Having a baby changes the way you view your in-laws. I love it when they come to visit now. They can hold the baby and I can go out.', 69183, 0), (434313, 'The more we learn, the more we will be confronted with decisions that we''ve never had to make before about life, about death, about parenting.', 69184, 0), (434314, 'I think a generation ago, dads went to work, they came home, and they had their dinner, had a drink, and then went to bed. I don''t know what it was like in your house, but that is how it was in mine. I think it is cool to have the dads in the trenches and doing the real parenting work.', 69185, 0), (434315, 'Being cool is being your own self, not doing something that someone else is telling you to do.', 67817, 0), (434316, 'Keep a cool head and maintain a low profile. Never take the lead - but aim to do something big.', 51676, 0), (434317, 'My key to dealing with stress is simple: just stay cool and stay focused.', 68254, 0), (434318, 'My sister is my little star, and I''m excited for her and proud of her. With her, I''m protective, but also I don''t want to be that sister who''s really pushy and thinks they know everything and making her feel like she doesn''t know what she''s doing. I''m trying to be that cool older sister and not the mom, but it''s hard.', 60670, 0), (434319, 'It''s cool to be different and just be who you are and shock people in a good way.', 22990, 0), (434320, 'Nothing is cooler and more attractive than a big comeback, and that''ll be me.', 67109, 0), (434321, 'I''m a mirror. If you''re cool with me, I''m cool with you, and the exchange starts. What you see is what you reflect. If you don''t like what you see, then you''ve done something. If I''m standoffish, that''s because you are.', 8650, 0), (434322, 'I''m not the kind of person who tries to be cool or trendy, I''m definitely an individual.', 68700, 0), (434323, 'I think it''s cool to be smart, and I think it''s sexy to be smart.', 69186, 0), (434324, 'I don''t want to be just known for the way I dress. I want to be known for how I play, how I treat people, and how I am as a role model. I don''t just want to be, ''He dresses cool'' or ''He dresses crazy.'' You''re going to have lovers and haters. I want my golf game to be the main thing.', 66920, 0), (434325, 'Keep a cool head and a warm heart.', 66962, 0), (434326, 'Picking a best friend who stands up for what she believes in, is true to herself and allows you to be yourself without judgement of how ''cool'' you are? Well, now you''re picking a friend for life.', 67625, 0), (434327, 'It''s so important to realize that every time you get upset, it drains your emotional energy. Losing your cool makes you tired. Getting angry a lot messes with your health.', 1206, 0), (434328, 'What people don''t understand is joining a gang ain''t bad, it''s cool, it''s fine. When you in the hood, joining a gang it''s cool because all your friends are in the gang, all your family''s in the gang. We''re not just killing people every night, we''re just hanging out, having a good time.', 15440, 0), (434329, 'My mom is just someone who''s easy to talk to and hang with. My sister, it''s always cool to be able to help her out with things. My brother is fun when we''re just joking and messing around. And my dad is someone who''s helpful with my music and easy to talk to about that stuff because he understands me in that sense.', 1573, 0), (434330, 'I think I''m cool. That''s all that matters.', 19593, 0), (434331, 'I think fashion is a lot of fun. I love clothes. More than fashion or brand labels, I love design. I love the thought that people put into clothes. I love when clothes make cultural statements and I think personal style is really cool. I also freely recognize that fashion should be a hobby.', 67062, 0), (434332, 'I don''t think of myself as hot or cool or anything, just a dork.', 69187, 0), (434333, 'I want to be a vampire. They''re the coolest monsters.', 358, 0), (434334, 'Cell phones, mobile e-mail, and all the other cool and slick gadgets can cause massive losses in our creative output and overall productivity.', 1172, 0), (434335, 'Jazz is smooth and cool. Jazz is rage. Jazz flows like water. Jazz never seems to begin or end. Jazz isn''t methodical, but jazz isn''t messy either. Jazz is a conversation, a give and take. Jazz is the connection and communication between musicians. Jazz is abandon.', 69188, 0), (434336, 'Good words cool more than cold water.', 64356, 0), (434337, 'To create well I have to be in a good mood, happy and cool.', 69189, 0), (434338, 'I''m cute - and God I hate that. Because that''s not cool. I''m like your niece, and nobody wants to date their niece. It''s the chubby cheeks. The whole reason people voted for me on American Idol is because I''m an everyday, normal girl.', 9111, 0), (434339, 'I wear sunglasses almost all the time outside - not because I think I''m really, really cool, but because of the rays.', 25405, 0), (434340, 'I think when you are a cool guy but also a hot guy, that makes you even more sexy.', 69190, 0), (434341, 'Rockets are cool. There''s no getting around that.', 10864, 0), (434342, 'I try to explain to people that the only way to be cool is to be who you truly are, and the only way to live life is to do the things that you want to do and be the person that you want to be no matter who that is or what that is or how you have to do it. That''s the only way you can be genuinely happy.', 20554, 0), (434343, 'Music is music, ultimately. If it makes you feel good, cool.', 12819, 0), (434344, 'For cool things to happen, you have to get out of your comfort zone.', 69191, 0), (434345, 'I am a bit of a bad boy. I have tattoos and I mess around. That''s part of my image, so it''s cool.', 329, 0), (434346, 'My main focus is to always try to be myself first, and then, hey, if I wear a cool jacket, that''s a bonus.', 68268, 0), (434347, 'For me, the cool thing is doing things that could only be done in gaming.', 69192, 0), (434348, 'A full beard looks cool.', 69193, 0), (434349, 'I never cut class. I loved getting A''s, I liked being smart. I liked being on time. I thought being smart is cooler than anything in the world.', 1997, 0), (434350, 'I suppose being fierce is a very good thing, and a very cool thing. But more than fierce, I think I''m a strong person and a strong individual. And that''s what I take with me every day.', 37495, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434351, 'Rhyme patterns are nothing without meanings to the words. A lot of rappers can do those flows, but the raps aren''t really about anything - which is cool sometimes, but to have the flow and the message is one of my favorite things.', 60269, 0), (434352, 'I like low-maintenance girls, but at the same time, classy. She needs to take care of herself. But also be a girl who isn''t afraid to get sweaty and play basketball, so it''s cool if she''s a tomboy.', 55068, 0), (434353, 'Rather be dead than cool.', 890, 0), (434354, 'The cool thing about being famous is traveling. I have always wanted to travel across seas, like to Canada and stuff.', 13881, 0), (434355, 'My biggest thing about being a role model is whatever I''m preaching, I''m practicing. If I''m telling people I''m boxing and then I''m eating a burger tonight, it''s because I am. I''m not cheating and eating a salad and then being like, ''Yeah! Burgers are cool!''', 60670, 0), (434356, 'If you''ve got cool nails, you wake up and you''re like, ''Oh, I''m happy now.''', 21196, 0), (434357, 'Remember the first time you went to a show and saw your favorite band. You wore their shirt, and sang every word. You didn''t know anything about scene politics, haircuts, or what was cool. All you knew was that this music made you feel different from anyone you shared a locker with. Someone finally understood you. This is what music is about.', 358, 0), (434358, 'I''m cool with failing so long as I know that there are people around me that love me unconditionally.', 13006, 0), (434359, 'There''s something cool about being a stealth classic.', 57404, 0), (434360, 'November is auspicious in so many parts of the country: the rice harvest is already in, the weather starts to cool, and the festive glow which precedes Christmas has began to brighten the landscape.', 16120, 0), (434361, 'My personal style falls between casual cool and meticulous slob. I''m most comfortable in jeans, but I love fashion.', 69194, 0), (434362, 'What I think is so amazing about having everything, and feeling like I have everything, is that I don''t really find happiness within materialistic things. Like, it''s cool if I can buy myself a new car, and I think it''s amazing for a week, but then the thrill is over, and I''m like, ''Oh, so I guess that wasn''t really happiness.''', 66658, 0), (434363, 'People look at me and see a calm, cool guy on the sidelines and I want them to know that my Christian faith affects my coaching and everything I do.', 4363, 0), (434364, 'It''s the most gratifying thing to have young girls telling me, ''I love that you do a photo shoot in pants and a button up shirt, and you still look cool.''', 69195, 0), (434365, 'I think you have to be cool to be a good flirt, and I don''t think I''m very cool.', 500, 0), (434366, 'I''m never quite cool, if you know what I mean. I''m basically the worst, best superhero.', 20849, 0), (434367, 'Black and awkward is the worst, because black people are stereotyped as being anything but awkward in mainstream media... Black people are always portrayed to be cool or overly dramatic, anything but awkward.', 68399, 0), (434368, 'Racism is taught in the home. We agree on that? Well, it''s very hard to teach racism to a teenager who''s listening to rap music and who idolizes, say, Snoop Dogg. It''s hard to say, ''That guy is less than you.'' The kid is like, ''I like that guy, he''s cool. How is he less than me?', 8650, 0), (434369, 'Sometimes just when I say hello the right way, I''m like, ''Whoa, I''m so cool.''', 68798, 0), (434370, 'The Internet is for haters. Everyone wants to knock somebody down, but it''s cool.', 67088, 0), (434371, 'When I hit 16, I got a scooter to ride to school. It was bright pink, and I saw on the ownership papers that Jonathan Ross once owned it. My friends slated me for it because of the colour, but it was cool. My father used to ride, and my mother''s boyfriend has a bike, so we''re a bit of a biker family.', 69196, 0), (434372, 'Saturday morning, you knew what was cool by what was on ''Soul Train.''', 67879, 0), (434373, 'The cool parts - the parts that have won Dubai its reputation as ''the Vegas of the Middle East'' or ''the Venice of the Middle East'' or ''the Disney World of the Middle East, if Disney World were the size of San Francisco and out in a desert'' - have been built in the last ten years.', 1047, 0), (434374, 'I kinda see everyone as competition. I''m a very competitive person. But I think that''s good. Competition is great. And as long as it''s friendly and not a malicious thing, then I think it''s cool.', 47095, 0), (434375, 'Sometimes it''s okay to give yourself a pat on the back and say, ''That was cool. That made me feel good.''', 69197, 0), (434376, 'The thing that I think a lot of guys need to know how to do is not take your mother''s advice about honesty being the best policy. Listen to your cool, drunk uncle who tells you to lie. Those are the relationships that last.', 68296, 0), (434377, 'I''m not the biggest motorcycle fan - they''re cool and a lot of fun, but they''re scary as well!', 69198, 0), (434378, 'Is a hippopotamus a hippopotamus, or just a really cool Opotamus?', 27687, 0), (434379, 'Me and my dad are friends. We''re cool. I''ll never be disappointed again, because I don''t expect anything anymore from him. I just let him exist, and that''s how we get along.', 22735, 0), (434380, 'I still have my school friends who are actually friends. It''s nice that they don''t think much about my singing career. They think it is cool, and they are happy for me, but they don''t really bother me about it. To them, I''m still just the schoolgirl from next door.', 67401, 0), (434381, 'I like cool jackets - a nice fall or winter coat. You can get a lot of use out of it, and you''ll wear it frequently, so it can really set the tone of your uniform for the season.', 28573, 0), (434382, 'I definitely move to the beat of my own drummer and man, he''s not playing something anyone has heard before. It''s pretty cool, though. Pretty cool.', 69199, 0), (434383, 'Growing up, I didn''t feel cool; I didn''t fit into any crowd.', 67561, 0), (434384, 'I try to be cool with everybody, but sometimes, everybody just has different personalities, motives, and different characters.', 69060, 0), (434385, 'There aren''t many things that are universally cool, and it''s cool not to litter. I''d never do it.', 2387, 0), (434386, 'If your stomach disputes you, lie down and pacify it with cool thoughts.', 5228, 0), (434387, 'I used to listen to ''Perfect Day'' by Hoku every single day in high school! ''On this perfect day, nothin'' standin'' in my way... Don''t you try to rain on my perfect day.'' It pumped me up when I was feeling down or defeated, whether it was from the cool kids making me feel left out or feeling overwhelmed with homework and mean teachers.', 69200, 0), (434388, 'Whatever hysteria exists is inflamed by mystery, suspicion and secrecy. Hard and exact facts will cool it.', 64538, 0), (434389, 'You can think of Hollywood as high school. TV actors are freshmen, comedy actors are maybe juniors, and dramatic actors - they''re the cool seniors.', 69201, 0), (434390, 'I haven''t experienced anything paranormal yet, but I did see what I think was a meteor light up the sky in a flash of red for a few seconds. That was really cool.', 69202, 0), (434391, 'It''s cool to be a part of recovery. This is just who I am, this is what I write about, what I do, and most of my work has been a reflection of what I''ve been going through in one way or another.', 60782, 0), (434392, 'I''m a geeky toy collector, and to have toys of your own characters is unbelievably cool.', 69203, 0), (434393, 'On stage, we just want to generate hysteria. We don''t care about looking cool or posing.', 69204, 0), (434394, 'I''d rate myself an 8. I do have my flaws, but I''m a cool dude. If I wasn''t myself, I''d kick it with me. I''m a down-to-earth person and all around cool guy.', 69205, 0), (434395, 'When I was younger, the pressure was just being cool. I never thought of myself as a cool guy. I always thought of myself as more of the goofy guy.', 55738, 0), (434396, 'I like to look cool and dress nice. Lil Uzi is a rock star. Just know that.', 69206, 0), (434397, 'I don''t count on the boy who waits till October, when it''s cool and fun, then decides he wants to play.', 62663, 0), (434398, 'Obviously anything that accessorizes or enhances the iPhone is always pretty cool.', 69207, 0), (434399, 'Pink is my favourite colour. I used to say my favourite colour was black to be cool, but it is pink - all shades of pink. If I have an accessory, it is probably pink.', 9530, 0), (434400, 'You show up in Paris, and on the drive from the airport to the hotel you''re like, ''This is so cool! I want to see something! I want to go to the Eiffel Tower!'' And then you leave the next morning. You think, Oh, I didn''t get to do anything. I tell people: I''ve been just about everywhere, but I''ve seen nothing.', 69198, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434401, 'How cool it is to see a bride walking down the aisle with a beautiful long gown with beautiful layers of tulle and organza, unveiling their mini dress at the party?', 67442, 0), (434402, 'I''m always inspired by people who have really cool Twitter profiles.', 69208, 0), (434403, 'It''s cool when fans spend so much time making things for me. It means a lot.', 957, 0), (434404, 'I''m just a cool type of guy who''s all about positives.', 67143, 0), (434405, 'It''s cool when people know you more, but I like people to treat me regular when they see me. I take pictures. I don''t really be big on people looking at me.', 69209, 0), (434406, 'I think I''m commercial underground. I''m not commercial in the way that people consider ''pop,'' but I''m not underground in the way that people consider that. either. I am just a cool guy.', 69210, 0), (434407, 'I think making friends is not being afraid to look stupid, because everyone wants a friend who is willing to be stupid and fun. If you try and be too cool, it only works in high school. After that, being uncool is a very cool thing to do. So just have fun, and don''t worry what other people think of you and people will want to be your friends.', 68296, 0), (434408, 'I''ve built a network that curates interestingness. In my universe, it encompasses thousands and thousands of filters and people, each person being a filter. So it''s kinda cool. Like I''ve created my own utopia, removing the boring stuff and showing only the amazing stuff.', 30570, 0), (434409, 'In the Middle East in the summertime, to keep cool, a lot of people sleep on the rooftops.', 69211, 0), (434410, 'Sketching in general - anywhere, not just in Gitmo, but in life, in the world - is a profoundly disruptive act. Because you''re creating something when you''re kind of expected to consume or sit passively. I''ve always sketched things as a way to get into them, whether it was a fancy nightclub or, you know, to have kids think I was cool, whatever.', 19819, 0), (434411, 'I do love Instagram, and my kids are with me, like, 24-7, so it''s inevitable that they''ll be on there. And honestly, I know it sounds weird, but I look up people all the time on it. Because I find people so interesting, and I''m curious about them. It''s a gateway to meet new people. I think the whole concept of Instagram is really cool.', 13881, 0), (434412, 'I''d rather be the cool aunt than the authoritative aunt.', 69212, 0), (434413, 'John Legend is a cool guy. He likes to chill, is easy to talk to and hang out with. He''s also inspiring on a musical level.', 69213, 0), (434414, 'As a young boy, I was taught in high school that hacking was cool.', 49891, 0), (434415, 'My perfect guy wears converse, is totally laid back, and doesn''t worry about being cool.', 793, 0), (434416, 'Jazz took too much discipline. You have to come in at the right place, which is different than me singing the blues, where I can sing, ''Oh, baby,'' if there''s a pause in the melody. With jazz, you better leave that space open, or put in something real cool.', 22852, 0), (434417, 'When you''re writing, you''re only a brain and some fingers, but drumming, you''re involving all four limbs, and you''re hearing stuff and you''re converting your ideas into physical motions, getting physical feedback from things you are touching - it''s pretty cool. It''s a really a nice contrast to writing.', 22759, 0), (434418, 'My mom gave me enough self-worth to carry me through difficult experiences. She was very loving and accepting. She was like, ''Whelp, you''re gay? OK, cool.''', 1860, 0), (434419, 'Be still and cool in thine own mind and spirit.', 3771, 0), (434420, 'All of my favorite people - people I really trust - none of them were cool in their younger years.', 100, 0), (434421, 'It''s not cool to be an alcoholic.', 60782, 0), (434422, 'We live in a world that tells us not to care, to consume everything in sight. It tells us that being cool and being an individual actually means buying what everyone else is buying and doing what everyone else is doing.', 69214, 0), (434423, 'Short boots are cool, in my humble opinion. They say, ''Hey! Winter is over, but summer hasn''t yet arrived - so enjoy this halfway point!''', 69076, 0), (434424, 'People will visit Mars, they will settle mars, and we should because it''s cool.', 22320, 0), (434425, 'When I first arrived in Baghdad in January 2003, I thought I would soon rent a house and envisioned myself swimming in the Tigris to cool off after reporting in the city the caliphs called Madinit al-Salam, the City of Peace. A year later, I realized I wouldn''t be taking any midnight dips - Madinat al-Salam no more.', 16377, 0), (434426, 'Vegetarians are cool. All I eat are vegetarians - except for the occasional mountain lion steak.', 68760, 0), (434427, 'I can take it. The tougher it gets, the cooler I get.', 9695, 0), (434428, 'One cool judgment is worth a thousand hasty counsels. The thing to do is to supply light and not heat.', 1970, 0), (434429, 'All women do have a different sense of sexuality, or sense of fun, or sense of like what''s sexy or cool or tough.', 1380, 0), (434430, 'It''s cool just because I''ve had this dream of changing the sport of swimming and it''s finally happening.', 30837, 0), (434431, 'I never saw music in terms of men and women or black and white. There was just cool and uncool.', 10602, 0), (434432, 'I wanted to escape Small Town U.S.A. To dismiss the boundaries, to explore. My life experience came from watching movies, TV, and reading books and magazines. When your culture comes from watching TV everyday, you''re bombarded with images of things that seem cool, places that seem interesting, people who have jobs and careers and opportunities.', 60178, 0), (434433, 'I think it would be cool if you were writing a ransom note on your computer, if the paper clip popped up and said, ''Looks like you''re writing a ransom note. Need help? You should use more forceful language, you''ll get more money.''', 2315, 0), (434434, 'I think all jocks have a sensitive side. It''s just, will they show it to anybody? Will they let their guard down and stop being tough and the cool jock guy around their friends, or just relax? I don''t know if it''s best to say opening up, but just relax and really say what you''re actually thinking, and not what you think people want to hear.', 68275, 0), (434435, 'These days it''s cool to be ethnic and to be different, but when I was a kid, it was not cool - at all. My friends would come over and my mom would make crepes with eggs, stuffed with mozzarella cheese, tomatoes and spinach. And they''d be like, ''What is this?''', 66406, 0), (434436, 'The cool thing about reading is that when you read a short story or you read something that takes your mind and expands where your thoughts can go, that''s powerful.', 100, 0), (434437, 'I''m a traditionalist, so for me, black coffee is cool.', 69215, 0), (434438, 'I''m cool with the way I look, I''m not an ugly dog, but I don''t see myself as a stud or anything.', 68360, 0), (434439, 'My Barbies were usually naked. Once, I took their heads off, cut their hair, drew on their short, spiky hair with some markers, then stuck the heads on Christmas lights. Every year, we''d string our tree with those Barbie heads. It looked demonic. My parents were so cool - they saw it as a form of self-expression.', 69216, 0), (434440, 'My style icons would be people like Brigitte Bardot and old Hollywood actresses who always look so stunning, cool and chic. I like classic and timeless looks.', 67131, 0), (434441, 'It''s like Canada is the little brother to the United States and one day they are going to show the world they''re just as cool as their successful big brother.', 69217, 0), (434442, 'As a person, I have a lot of different sides to me, and I genuinely just embrace them. I don''t think, ''Oh, I gotta put on my cool face now!''', 69218, 0), (434443, 'We were in recycling before recycling was cool.', 69219, 0), (434444, 'The ballplayer who loses his head, who can''t keep his cool, is worse than no ballplayer at all.', 69220, 0), (434445, 'I want you to see that I''m looking. Look at me look at you. I''m cool with that.', 69221, 0), (434446, 'It''s cool to go places where working people are happy.', 1082, 0), (434447, 'I''m a Muslim, but I think Jesus would have a drink with me. He would be cool. He would talk to me.', 11133, 0), (434448, 'So when I got to be about 13 or 14, I started listening - even though my parents music was way cool - to contemporary hard rock at that time, which was Aerosmith, Cheap Trick, Black Sabbath, AC/DC, Ted Nugent and all that, and that''s just where I came from.', 22833, 0), (434449, 'I''m doing everything that I can, working with experts, really studying the statistics to figure out a way we can make it cool or normal to be kind and loving.', 47, 0), (434450, 'I once sang ''Summer Nights,'' from ''Grease,'' at a bar in Melbourne with John Travolta, who''s a good friend of mine. He looked cool singing the part of Danny - sitting in an armchair, smoking a cigar - while I got stuck playing Sandy.', 43985, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434451, 'It''s cool to be healthy.', 39403, 0), (434452, 'In my hometown there is a pub named after me - The Frome Flyer on Jenson Avenue. How cool is that?!', 69222, 0), (434453, 'I''ve always been scared of advertising folk. I''ve met them at parties and I''ve been to their offices and I''ve always found them intimidatingly cool. At one company I visited, they held their meetings in a caravan that had somehow been installed in the place, a rather more exotic place to gather than the typical BBC glass box.', 69223, 0), (434454, 'It was just an idea I had, that it could be cool to have a book covered in fake fur.', 444, 0), (434455, 'If people are taking pictures of me at Starbucks, it''s not the end of the world. It''s cool, it''s fun, it''s exciting.', 67523, 0), (434456, 'Summer is a great time to visit art museums, which offer the refreshing rinse of swimming pools - only instead of cool water, you immerse yourself in art.', 19958, 0), (434457, 'Being in love is not cool!', 69224, 0), (434458, 'When you think back to your first kiss, your hair is perfect and she was wearing a cool outfit. We remember it with restraint and we remember it with style. We remember it as idealistically as you can think.', 6, 0), (434459, 'I have visualizations where I''m living in a really cool place - probably outside of town - with a really dope studio where I can record music or film things. Just have my own mini production house. That''s really the thing I''d love to end up with the most and only do gigs when I needed to and also amass a little bit of a crew around me.', 68050, 0), (434460, 'I want to speak up and tell you that mascara and clothes don''t make you cool, neither do name-brand handbags, but being a leader can.', 67625, 0), (434461, 'I would love to work with Marion Cotillard... and my sister! I''ve never worked with Dakota before in a movie. It''d be so cool to be on screen interacting with each other one day. It will happen, I''m just not sure when.', 69225, 0), (434462, 'I''m a girl''s girl. I''m a woman''s woman. I''m a cool girl.', 69226, 0), (434463, 'Maybe the coolest people are the ones who don''t care about being cool.', 47094, 0), (434464, 'I''m a farmer now, and it''s fantastic. My goal is to be totally self-sufficient and grow everything that I eat. There''s something about earning your dinner that''s cool.', 18054, 0), (434465, 'Barcelona is one of my favourite cities in the world. The fashion and people are just so effortlessly cool.', 69227, 0), (434466, 'I''m cool with Jay-Z. Jay-Z is genuinely my friend.', 22735, 0), (434467, 'I had a couple of really cool friends when I was a kid, and we''d find cool music and movies and show them to each other. My friend Dennis had a copy of ''A Clockwork Orange'' and he''d already seen it once, and he was like, ''We need to watch this.'' I was sleeping over his house - and I think we were literally 15 - and we watched it.', 358, 0), (434468, 'You''ve got to be strong enough for love. It''s very easy to be cool and cynical. It''s very difficult to just let yourself go and be in love. You''ve got to be strong enough for that.', 13014, 0), (434469, 'I really want to do a film in another language. My dad''s from Germany, so it''d be really cool to do a film in German. I''m not quite fluent, but I can get there. And my accent''s pretty good. I wouldn''t feel too out of my element.', 68430, 0), (434470, 'I''m glad to see that BMW is bringing an electric car to market. That''s cool.', 10864, 0), (434471, 'Unwanted honking not only irritates others, but may also end up causing accidents. Drivers lose cool and it may result in road rage.', 69228, 0), (434472, 'I''ve done a road trip across Italy with a girlfriend, and that was very romantic. I think that road trips are probably one of the romantic things you can do. To take your girlfriend and just stay wherever; don''t have a destination and just drive and see where the road takes you is pretty cool.', 69229, 0), (434473, 'I go from English to Spanish, and I feel I have some cool songs.', 65079, 0), (434474, 'I once asked Ozzy Osbourne, truly one of my favorite people in the world, if he was cool with singing Black Sabbath songs year after year, whether he was performing with Black Sabbath or out on a solo tour. He said it was great.', 68, 0), (434475, 'As far as putting stuff on social media, I think Instagram is really cool because I like the visual aspect. You''re taking pictures, and you can put a filter on them, and it''s super creative.', 35810, 0), (434476, 'I love to hear a cool ambient sound at runway shows. It creates a good energy.', 67009, 0), (434477, 'When I have a good pair of shoes, I wear them over and over. Whether it''s nice sneakers or a cool pair of combat boots, splurge on a pair you love that you can wear over and over with totally different outfits.', 69230, 0), (434478, 'I''m born and raised in Mexico. I only spent eight months in the States, but definitely English is a really big part of my life, and I love it. Thank God my mom put me in American school because I''m able to be working in the States, and it opens a lot more doors being half and not being only one. It''s cool because I get to turn it on and off.', 69231, 0), (434479, 'I don''t follow anything that''s said about him much, but the Uwe Boll that I know is just a really cool guy. He''s just a really quiet, kind and passionate filmmaker who really believes in what he''s doing. Like any director that an actor wants to work with, you want a director who''s passionate and believes in the work that he''s doing.', 69232, 0), (434480, 'If kids can have some sort of social responsibility, that''s cool. But if they''re not actually having social responsibility, and they''re kind of hiding behind it, that''s kind of useless, or even worse.', 69233, 0), (434481, 'I feel like my style''s always been influenced by ''less is more.'' The coolest styles are kind of simple and classic, like a white T-shirt and jeans. Maybe you have a cool belt and cool shoes, but everything else you keep simple.', 23824, 0), (434482, 'When I am working on a book or a story, I write every morning as soon after first light as possible. There is no one to disturb you, and it is cool or cold, and you come to your work and warm as you write.', 110, 0), (434483, 'Fashion is really a place where every other industry connects, whether it''s music or acting. At the end of the day, everyone is going to walk the red carpet and be interested in the fashion side of it. I think that''s really cool because as a model, you get to connect with a lot of different worlds.', 60670, 0), (434484, 'I guess I''ve always been a groupie. My first date was a bull rider called Tommy Lee Bryant. We''d go to the rodeo every Saturday and Sunday. The bull riders were the cool guys.', 65023, 0), (434485, 'Just sharing music with each other - that''s cool. It''s the selling that becomes the problem.', 12819, 0), (434486, 'For me, being comfortable is the best way to express my personality. Some days I like to be chill and wear my Stan Smiths with a cool little jacket, a blouse, and some lipstick for night, and that''s it.', 69234, 0), (434487, 'The last game I played in college was in the NIT against St. Mary''s. That was the first time I had come to the Oakland area. So, the last game I played in college and the first game of my NBA career were out here in the Bay Area. It''s pretty cool.', 69121, 0), (434488, 'My favorite was the one about ''Snow White''. Those funky little guys with the beards. The poisonous apple. And that cool mirror the evil stepmother used to talk to. You know, she''d ask it all these questions: Who''s the nicest? Who''s the sweetest... Who''s the fairest of them all? And for a while, everything was hunky-dory.', 69235, 0), (434489, 'Me and my buddies are all like brothers. So it''s okay for us to say ''I love you'' or whatever. It''s always cool. I think that comes from my dad. That''s just the way he always was.', 55738, 0), (434490, 'When I''m singing, it''s a mixture of my innocence in the projects, my mom and dad. It''s all the good and the bad, the laughs and the frowns that I went through and seen other people go through. Then you be trying to write it. Whatever''s coming out, you try and make it all cool.', 67027, 0), (434491, 'Being a sex symbol isn''t cool unless you''re in love with a girl, and she calls you a sex symbol.', 69236, 0), (434492, 'This was something I always dreamed and wanted to be part of, when women''s wrestling was freakin'' cool, and now it is.', 69237, 0), (434493, 'Accessories are key - nothing beats a cool Panama hat or statement shades - look to Maison Michel or Miu Miu for inspiration.', 69238, 0), (434494, 'Living my life socially means there is a swagger to how I dress, walk; it''s not about being ''cool,'' it''s just being me - that''s understanding your place and your center - that''s what swagger is, and I guess that''s where the soul comes from.', 67890, 0), (434495, 'Drake is an amazing person. Also, a magician. He''s a big brother, super-talent; he''s cool.', 69239, 0), (434496, 'The Internet made fame wack and anonymity cool.', 22945, 0), (434497, 'What''s really cool about LEGOs is that you can put a bunch of bricks on the table, and everybody will make something different. Everyone has different ideas, and some of them may seem crazy.', 69240, 0), (434498, 'The worst thing I could be thinking is how could I be a cool bass player.', 69241, 0), (434499, 'I''m more into the Spawn toys. They''re really cool. They''re coming out with a Techno Spawn series and another series, The Dark Ages, which are really cool.', 69242, 0), (434500, 'Everyone is different, but I''m not standoffish at all. I''m not one of those people who prefer to write a note. I''ll walk right up to you and ask you out! Even if the answer''s no, I''m totally cool with it.', 69243, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434501, 'When people recognise me they just kind of go ''Hi how are you,'' really kind of cool you know.', 69244, 0), (434502, 'Americans are cool; if you show just a chink of vulnerability, they respond so much. They''ll pat you on the arm and say, ''Hey kid, you''re all right.'' Brits will respond but they are much more cynical.', 9272, 0), (434503, 'I''m not Rihanna. I''m not cool. When people come up to me in the street, they often want a hug, not a photo, and they want that because they like my work.', 67062, 0), (434504, 'I went to high school, and I started getting bullied because I was very weird. I mean, freshman year I went to school in a pirate suit - I just didn''t care. I''m not like the cool girls - I''m the other girl. The one that''s basically a nerd, but proud of that.', 69245, 0), (434505, 'I went to a public school through sixth grade, and being good at tests wasn''t cool.', 1133, 0), (434506, 'That''s the thing about Aquaman that''s cool is he''s not an alien, right? He''s from our planet, and he''s from a society that we''re not privy to in the context of the story.', 69246, 0), (434507, 'The Tom Brady sandwich would be a prosciutto with a nice Buffalo mozzarella, on a crispy baguette with a little fresh basil. Brady is classy; he''s a really cool dude. He''s got a lot of flavor.', 69247, 0), (434508, 'I created ''Rookie'' because I read a lot of websites that I thought were cool and interesting, but they weren''t for teens, and I wanted us to have something that could be ours.', 32663, 0), (434509, 'I''m a very basic dresser. I''m not interested in calling too much attention to myself. I like to look cool without being too noticeable.', 433, 0), (434510, 'I think it''s cool that London Fashion Week is about young designers trying wacky things.', 45044, 0), (434511, '''Boyz-n-the-Hood'' was actually supposed to be written for Eazy''s group. He had a group out in New York called Home Boys Only, called HBO. One of them looked like LL Cool J. Eazy wanted to write a song for them, a street song, like what we were doing on the mix tapes. So when I wrote it, it was too West Coast for them.', 26404, 0), (434512, 'If you''re doing this because you feel like you have a burning desire to do it, then you''ll find a way to do it, no matter what. If you''re doing this because you''re thinking, ''Hey, this will be really cool. I''ll be famous. I''ll be on YouTube,'' then you''ll probably quit, because it''s not easy to do for the long haul.', 56, 0), (434513, 'Cyber attacks are not what makes the cool war ''cool.'' As a strategic matter, they do not differ fundamentally from older tools of espionage and sabotage.', 68675, 0), (434514, 'People in high school either feel like they''re with the cool kids in a clique, or they''re isolated - there''s no in-between.', 69248, 0), (434515, 'I was not a cool kid. There was no reason for me to be marginalised. I was just a nerd. I was kind of weird, and I found solace in video games.', 68196, 0), (434516, 'Tracy Morgan is subdued. I''m cool. I''m chilled out.', 68238, 0), (434517, 'Making a mix CD - albeit slightly old school - is generally a pretty cool gift and something I like to receive, or giving someone a book that moved you. Writing an inscription inside makes it even better.', 69249, 0), (434518, 'We do this basically for ourselves. People appreciate it, which is cool, but I think they appreciate that we''re doing it for ourselves. We''re doing it our way, and how people like it is not up to us. We like it.', 13043, 0), (434519, 'It''s a funny thing. I''ll be in my home town of Columbus at a restaurant or something, and the waiter maybe asks, ''What do you do?'' and I say, ''Oh, I''m in a band... Twenty One Pilots,'' and he''ll say, ''Cool, I''ll check it out. I never heard of them.'' And then I say, ''In September we''re playing the Schottenstein Center,'' and it''s like, ''What?!''', 69250, 0), (434520, 'I always preferred to hang out with the outcasts, ''cause they were cooler; they had better taste in music, for one thing, I guess because they had more time to develop one with the lack of social interaction they had!', 55317, 0), (434521, 'Keep cool anger is not an argument. ', 3308, 0), (434522, 'I just think it looks so cool when a woman has a dirty martini. She looks so powerful.', 69251, 0), (434523, 'My parents are the coolest of the cool on every single level, and it''s because they have a deep appreciation for every moment of their lives.', 18940, 0), (434524, 'I was trying to be this person who is cool, eternally rocking.', 4019, 0), (434525, 'Oh, my God, this amazing cool breeze is coming through my window and the sun is shining. I''m happy.', 69252, 0), (434526, 'I do really silly dancing. I love dancing, but I''m not cool when I dance. It''s not about my moves, it''s not about how cool I am, it''s not about how slick I look on the dance floor, it''s about having a great time.', 22754, 0), (434527, 'Prince turned experimental music into pop music. ''When Doves Cry,'' the whole ''Purple Rain'' soundtrack - he was inspired by the Cocteau Twins and new wave pop and brought it into R&B when he first started, and then it became this cool, next-level, kind of hard-to-digest music. Which is what I felt ''House of Balloons'' was.', 23049, 0), (434528, 'You think aerobics is not a cool sport? I think you are wrong. It requires amazing discipline - flexibility, fitness, knowledge. And you have to do it with a big smile on your face. Also, I once performed in front of 10,000 screaming women. I tell you something, I''d rather do that than kick a ball around in front of a few men.', 69253, 0), (434529, 'When I was doing ''Smile,'' I was looking back at pictures of myself and going, ''Thank goodness I couldn''t do the sprayed-bangs thing! Everybody''s so embarrassed by that hairstyle now, but I was never cool enough to pull it off!''', 69254, 0), (434530, 'Reggae, oh man. It''s the ultimate music. The positivity. The musicality. The whole cultural expressionism of it. The danceability. Just the cool factor. The melody factor. Some of it comes from a religious place. If there were a competition of who makes the best religious music, it would definitely be the Rastafarian reggae.', 68942, 0), (434531, 'I wish I was a cool guy and could drink coffee black, but I put almond milk and raw cane sugar in it.', 68953, 0), (434532, 'My family lived off the land and summer evening meals featured baked stuffed tomatoes, potato salad, corn on the cob, fresh shelled peas and homemade ice cream with strawberries from our garden. With no air conditioning in those days, the cool porch was the center of our universe after the scorching days.', 69255, 0), (434533, 'It''s actually cool to be positive and optimistic and idealistic. It''s cool to see yourself doing beautiful, great things.', 68386, 0), (434534, 'It''s just so cool when you meet people who are different than you are. That can give you a different perspective, a viewpoint on life, or inspire you. I mean, what would the world be like if we were all the same? I think it would be very boring.', 69256, 0), (434535, 'I wouldn''t want to be Superman. Batman would be cool. But the one I''ve always wanted to play is the Joker. There is a maniacal and dangerous side to me.', 67691, 0), (434536, 'With all of you men out there who think that having a thousand different ladies is pretty cool, I have learned in my life I''ve found out that having one woman a thousand different times is much more satisfying.', 59443, 0), (434537, 'The battle to find a workplace that''s wheelchair accessible is a feat in itself, let alone an employer who''s going to be cool about employing someone with a disability in a job you actually want to do.', 67675, 0), (434538, 'I''m like a big 10-year-old when I''m on stage. I just go up there and do whatever I think is cool at the moment.', 19593, 0), (434539, 'I feel that we, as Indians, have a knack for loving a stereotypical, sobbing, sympathy-seeking personality. I feel that we need to promote quirky, cool and youthful talent. We have to stop propagating the sob-story angle of celebs, where they try to be larger-than-life. That is very outdated. It is so boring that it puts you to sleep.', 67017, 0), (434540, 'If we have a great idea, we''ll go, ''Oh, this could be a cool movie.'' Or really for us, it''s more like, ''Oh, this is a really bad idea. Let''s do this. This seems really stupid.''', 6876, 0), (434541, 'Heroes don''t wear diapers. It''s just not cool.', 8453, 0), (434542, 'I want kids of this generation to see that everything is cool, that there''s some kind of unity in hip-hop. We all found something that''s really important to us, and music is all we''ve really got.', 69257, 0), (434543, 'I know that people think I''m sexy and I am looked at as that. It is cool with me. It''s wonderful to have sexy appeal. If you embrace it, it can be a very beautiful thing.', 69258, 0), (434544, 'If I could have anyone on speed dial it would be George Clooney. He seems like a cool guy who would give good advice.', 69259, 0), (434545, 'Survival, in the cool economics of biology, means simply the persistence of one''s own genes in the generations to follow.', 3484, 0), (434546, 'No-one has ever called me a cool dude. I''m somewhere between geek and normal.', 2333, 0), (434547, 'I realized that if I don''t like something, I can change it. If I don''t feel comfortable with something, then I have a voice to say it''s not cool.', 68211, 0), (434548, 'What''s really cool about our family is that we don''t hold grudges, and I think that is what''s been the key to the success. We get into our little disagreements, and whether we''re right or wrong, we''ll go and apologize. That''s just the way we are.', 67299, 0), (434549, 'To act coolly, intelligently and prudently in perilous circumstances is the test of a man - and also a nation.', 69260, 0), (434550, 'My problem was that I was blond. There were no heroes with blond hair. Robert Taylor and Henry Fonda, they all had dark hair. The only one I found was Van Johnson, who wasn''t too cool. He was a nice, homely American boy. So I created my own image. It worked.', 40738, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434551, 'Being uncool is being pretty much the coolest you can be.', 8055, 0), (434552, 'Music is for people. The word ''pop'' is simply short for popular. It means that people like it. I''m just a normal jerk who happens to make music. As long as my brain and fingers work, I''m cool.', 22690, 0), (434553, 'I''m always drawing, so Draw Something is a cool game to play against your friends when you''re bored and sat chilling out and relaxing.', 329, 0), (434554, 'As far as rap goes, I grew up in Hollis, Queens, so early influences were people like Run DMC and LL Cool J.', 67882, 0), (434555, 'I''m not trying to be this cool girl. If you''re trying to be something you''re not, it''s slowly going to bite you in the butt.', 69261, 0), (434556, 'It''s the same with visual arts, you have some really cool, wonderful striking images that make you think and then again you have wonderful striking images that just take you away from the existing world for a second. And I like the latter a bit more.', 69262, 0), (434557, 'I''ve been in fights, but that doesn''t make me cool or like a tough guy or more interesting actor, I''m not proud of it.', 66795, 0), (434558, 'When you''re a kid, you see your parents reading the newspaper and you''re like, ''God, why are they reading the newspaper?'' When you''re young, you''re not reading the newspaper. But there comes a time in your life when the newspaper''s cool.', 69263, 0), (434559, 'Sure, climbing Mount Everest would be cool, but that''s something I would now like to do as a family. Big experiences like that I don''t want to have on my own anymore. I want to share them.', 69264, 0), (434560, 'We found out the Gemini spacesuit was, well, oxygen was flowing to keep me cool as well as to breathe, and it wasn''t good enough. My visor got fogged.', 68305, 0), (434561, 'The funny thing is, the girls that I''m always up against for roles are pretty nice and cool, like Emma Watson. She''s awesome.', 69265, 0), (434562, 'And we have a little herb garden, which survived the winter thanks to global warming. It makes me feel like a cool, old Italian housewife, that I kept my rosemary alive outside all winter.', 20, 0), (434563, 'There''s a gap between what I want to do, what I do on camera, and what gets edited. Right? So the goal is to try and close the gaps. What''s the biggest compliment is if I read a review and it''s exactly what I wrote down in my diary before ever filming it. That''s really cool. That''s the biggest signifier of closing the gaps.', 2387, 0), (434564, 'I used to love being the class clown. I loved to make jokes and make people laugh. There was a set of students who would find it funny. But the cool students were like, ''Eeew!''', 68399, 0), (434565, 'One thing that has helped me to become patient and cool is that I grew up with sisters.', 25162, 0), (434566, 'My mom is my best friend in the entire world. She is so cool and so inspiring. I''ve always been able to be open with her and talk to her as a friend.', 69266, 0), (434567, 'I''m not very cool. I have a really hard time meeting people and stuff.', 69267, 0), (434568, 'I always say, ''Hip-hop takes me everywhere.'' It''s crazy when I step onstage, and people might not speak much English, but they know every word to your songs. It''s kind of freaky, but it''s really cool.', 69268, 0), (434569, 'Many in the world are searching, often intensely, for a source of refreshment that will quench their yearning for meaning and direction in their lives. They crave a cool, satisfying drink of insight and knowledge that will soothe their parched souls.', 4294, 0), (434570, 'You''re going to be way happier doing what you actually love and finding other people that love the same thing than doing something that other people love so you''re just cooler and you have cool friends.', 69269, 0), (434571, 'It''s going to be interesting to see how society deals with artificial intelligence, but it will definitely be cool.', 69270, 0), (434572, 'I had my bad-boy moment in my teens. I''ll never do that again. It wasn''t pleasant, and I learned my lesson. It was sexy and mysterious, and it''s like, ''Look how cool they are,'' but it''s just not worth it. He was lying to me and accusing me of cheating - but then I realized he was the one cheating.', 69216, 0), (434573, 'In this beginner-friendly book, called ''Learn to Program with Minecraft,'' you will learn how to do cool things in Minecraft using the Python programming language. No prior programming experience is needed.', 68983, 0), (434574, 'To me, a sure-fire way to get in a rut is by sitting around playing by yourself for too long. You''ve gotta get out there and jam, man! You don''t have to necessarily be in a band, all you''ve gotta have are a couple of buds who play too. They don''t have to be guitarists either; jamming with a bassist or a drummer is cool.', 69271, 0), (434575, 'We may never be as big as WWE, but the cool thing about TNA is that we are the alternative. So people who get tired and bored with the WWE - I''ve been there, I understand - there''s an alternative and something else to watch.', 46139, 0), (434576, 'I''m proud to be part of the fabric that inspires the next generations to remain curious and remember that ''smart is cool.''', 68047, 0), (434577, 'I''m keeping the pixie. I hope I inspire people... it''s really cool to have short hair.', 69272, 0), (434578, 'I think when you''re winning, your uniforms are cool.', 69273, 0), (434579, 'You know, you grow up with the image of John Travolta being super cool - ''Saturday Night Fever,'' Brian De Palma, handsome young god... he, in reality, is a very silly man. And I mean that in a good way. He''ll walk around the set talking in little weird voices, making people laugh.', 68670, 0), (434580, 'With ''The Social Network,'' I got into it at first because frankly I thought there was a cool courtroom drama to be had with the intellectual properties. And then what further drew me in was that the most extraordinary social networking device ever created was created by the world''s most antisocial person. I liked that story.', 1482, 0), (434581, 'But this is Miami, you can''t come to Miami and not show any skin. You gotta show something. If you''re all covered up in this heat, you''re gonna make me pass out out just to look at you. It''s sweaty in Miami-but the diamonds will keep me cool.', 67665, 0), (434582, 'The thing about stand-up was, I was doing all this sketch and YouTube stuff where I was not being censored and I got to do my own thing, and it was really cool.', 20007, 0), (434583, 'When you try to cool down hot emotions, what tends to happen is that you end up either repressing them or losing them altogether. Neither is desirable. Without emotion, much social interaction loses its meaning or changes for the worse.', 67531, 0), (434584, 'At Tencent, we may be businessmen, but we are still chasing our IT, our science. We are still striving to create something really cool, trying to create things we couldn''t even imagine without our new technologies. I am still clinging to this enthusiasm.', 69274, 0), (434585, 'I like Kauffman Stadium in Kansas City. With the waterfall and things like that, I think it''s pretty cool.', 69275, 0), (434586, 'Trajectories aren''t linear. Life''s just a roller coaster. If you''re getting a chance to do cool stuff, and it''s varied stuff, just enjoy it. I guess I''m a believer in the randomness of life rather than it being a linear trajectory or an arc, a consistent smooth arc, towards anything.', 67881, 0), (434587, 'The simple truth is that balding African-American men look cool when they shave their heads, whereas balding white men look like giant thumbs.', 2223, 0), (434588, 'I just tried to keep my cool and continue with my race plan: to win.', 66918, 0), (434589, 'I don''t go to the cool, trendy restaurants. I go to either the holes in the wall or the super-fancy restaurants where there are no cool people.', 1725, 0), (434590, 'I''ve never been cool - and I don''t care.', 25462, 0), (434591, 'I''m from Iowa, we don''t know what cool is!', 20099, 0), (434592, 'And not only that, I also have the MacBook Air which is really cool. Even my wife is jealous of my MacBook Air.', 69276, 0), (434593, 'I used to lie between cool, clean sheets at night after I''d had a bath, after I had washed my hair and scrubbed my knuckles and finger-nails and teeth. Then I could lie quite still in the dark with my face to the window with the trees in it, and talk to God.', 52944, 0), (434594, 'The cool thing is that now that people have made this evolution where cooking is cool, people are doing it on weekends, they''re doing their own challenges. It''s back to cooking. And it''s real cooking.', 69277, 0), (434595, 'In the Lamborghini I have to avoid certain roads because of pot holes, and there''s nowhere to put my drink, no cup holder. And I''m not going to lie, it looks pretentious. I used to think it was cool to, like, drive it to dinner. Now? Like I really need to be looked at any more.', 69278, 0), (434596, 'We''re always bombarded with images from magazines of what looks cool and sexy.', 66921, 0), (434597, 'Sometimes life''s so much cooler when you just don''t know any better and all the painful lessons have not hammered your head open yet.', 3498, 0), (434598, 'An orange on the table, your dress on the rug, and you in my bed, sweet present of the present, cool of night, warmth of my life.', 5866, 0), (434599, 'I try not to name too many labels - not because it''s not cool, but because it starts getting political.', 69117, 0), (434600, 'I shall go the way of the open sea, to the lands I knew before you came, and the cool ocean breezes shall blow from me the memory of your name.', 69279, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434601, 'It''s cool to have critical success because it''s always nice for your peers to say, ''Good job.'' But who cares about them?', 69280, 0), (434602, 'I was training more learning how to scuba dive which I''d never done which was really, really, really cool.', 69281, 0), (434603, 'Now, guitar was pretty cool. Everybody knew something on the guitar. So I wanted to play guitar, but I told my dad if he wanted me to keep studying something, I''d like to study piano.', 2152, 0), (434604, 'When Brian told me he grew up in New Mexico, I told him I thought it is cool that people from other countries play football. He corrected me on my geography and agreed to sit down with me anyway.', 67040, 0), (434605, 'One of the great bands we opened up for was Priest back in ''89. That was really great because at that time we had never met them, never toured with them before. They were a big influence on Slayer, so to open up for them was really cool.', 69282, 0), (434606, 'Well, a sort of epiphany: I was in a great band. And it''s very cool to be at 53 and realise that when you were a kid you were in a great band.', 69283, 0), (434607, 'If you want to go to the mall, you have to take security. But it''s always cool. The kids are amazing.', 69258, 0), (434608, 'I read the script for Wonder Boys, and I said that was almost perfect, it was so classy, cool and funny. It''s a really specific thing. We stuck to it, it turned out good and a lot of people liked it.', 69284, 0), (434609, 'Where I come from it was really unheard of to be at a party and someone says, ''What kind of music do you make?'', and you say, ''Pop music.'' You may as well have ''I''m not cool'' stamped on your forehead.', 47, 0), (434610, 'I try to explain to people that you get the roles that are right when they''re right. If you have a nerd character but you''re kind of a cool guy, you''re probably not going to get the nerd part. The nerd is going to get the nerd part. You know, someone like me.', 69285, 0), (434611, 'You have to be the best of whatever you are, but successful, cool actresses come in all shapes and sizes.', 66826, 0), (434612, 'Fame and stuff like that is all very cool, but at the end of the day, we''re all human beings. Although what I do is incredibly surreal and fun and amazing and I''m really grateful for it, I don''t believe my own press release, do you know what I mean?', 69286, 0), (434613, 'I think working with Johnny Depp was very intimidating. It was my fault though. I mean he''s a total cool nice, nice guy, but I was just so, I don''t know, overpowered by his presence. Like he''s a very mystic person. He''s older so I never really warmed up around him. I was so stiff.', 69287, 0), (434614, 'I''m a big techno fan. I love that thumping kick drum. We heard a version of ''Lost in Love'' and it was thrash metal. It sounded cool!', 69288, 0), (434615, 'I remember being on film sets when I was younger, and only men got to do the cool action movies. So I thought, ''Maybe I''ll get to produce one day and get to do cool stuff too,'' which is what happened when we did ''Charlie''s Angels.'' Starting my production company was a big turning point for me.', 292, 0), (434616, 'If you meet a girl, you meet a girl. It''s normal, so if you exchange numbers, whatevs, it''s cool.', 329, 0), (434617, 'Violence is a very ugly thing. Violence is often so casual on film, and made to look so cool and so sexy, but violence is a repulsive, repugnant act that human beings inflict on each other. It shouldn''t seem to be cool and sexy, ever really.', 69289, 0), (434618, '''Aladdin'' was probably my favorite Disney animation when I was a kid. The animation was great and Robin Williams was unbelievable as the Genie. ''Aladdin'' was an amazing adventure and the lead character was a hero for guys, which I loved. It wasn''t a princess or a girl beating the odds; it was a street rat. That seemed really cool to me.', 69290, 0), (434619, 'As far as friendships go, things change even without the fame. People start moving on. I have a few friends that are married and are starting to have kids and I''m like, ''Oh my goodness gracious - that''s so insane.'' I also have friends who are just doing their own thing, which is cool.', 67069, 0), (434620, 'I think it''s interesting to have a cool character not look so cool, you know?', 69291, 0), (434621, 'My niece was very much caught up in the vampire craze for young adults, and she thought having a vampire boyfriend would be a cool thing. What do you do on a first date? The more I thought about it, the more fun I had imagining what you''d serve a vampire for dinner.', 6554, 0), (434622, 'New diseases like SARS and bird flu cause anxiety in the community. People get worried, some to the extent that it even affects their health. You feel very sad, and yet you must carry on and maintain your cool in very trying and difficult moments. You have to tough it out.', 69292, 0), (434623, 'I''m thinking, ''Man, there''s this whole other group of people that are attached to me because of my last name and my family''s roots.'' That''s pretty cool. That''s special, that''s a lot of power and it''s important.', 69293, 0), (434624, 'I don''t view Twitter as a promotional tool but as a really, really, really cool cocktail party.', 3327, 0), (434625, 'Perfect heroes are cool, but no one can really empathize or identify with them.', 691, 0), (434626, 'When The Daily Muse initially wanted to launch a job board, our first ideas were insanely (and needlessly) complex. We wanted to integrate with social networks, gather rich personal data to build predictive algorithms, and put together numerous cool visualization tools before launching out to the world. We were just sure users would love it!', 67682, 0), (434627, 'I don''t go out drinking and stuff like that. My friends say ''Just have one drink, JD.'' I say ''What''s the point?'' I''ll go to a club and have a Red Bull, get my buzz. And the next day I feel cool. It''s discipline, not just with drinking but a lot of things in life. You''ve just got to look at the bigger picture.', 69294, 0), (434628, 'The world needs actual excitement and emotion more than it needs cool people.', 11813, 0), (434629, 'I was just a big fan of tattoos always growing up, and I wanted something cool that symbolizes what I''ve been through in my life, and everything on my chest and my back is like a collage.', 1900, 0), (434630, 'I remember my first run-in with cops. It took me really getting to hang, well after that, with cops who were cool, and realizing, ''Okay, there are some bad ones.'' I ran into some bad ones in Columbus, Ohio, but they''re not all bad.', 68702, 0), (434631, 'When you make a book or you make a movie, it is almost like hitting on somebody. It''s not because you want to seduce people that you will seduce them; you can hit on somebody and it doesn''t work. But when you hit on them and it works, then it''s really cool.', 2030, 0), (434632, 'I don''t need to come back to Wimbledon every year because I can''t live without it. I''d be totally cool without tennis.', 67701, 0), (434633, 'The world that I am coming from, hip-hop, is so regurgitated and repetitive that some people are used to that and they don''t want change, they don''t like change. And I get that, that''s cool. Luckily for me, I''m confident in myself as an artist where I can do what I want, and as long as I''m cool with it, I''m cool with it.', 69295, 0), (434634, 'I first met my husband when I was 15. He was very cool, in a band, all that kind of thing, but he took a long time to grow up. Our paths crossed again 10 years later, and after about two weeks I knew that was it. I''m glad I met him when I did, even though I was fairly young. Because I think sometimes you can crystallise into singledom.', 69296, 0), (434635, 'I met Bill Clinton; he''s a very nice guy. Yeah, Bill Clinton''s cool.', 1451, 0), (434636, 'My dad probably gave me the best advice growing up. I think it''s really just keeping your cool in situations and learning to balance everything.', 66915, 0), (434637, 'Being incarcerated is truly very serious, and it has changed my life to such an extent that breaking the cycle has become my sole focus. Jail is definitely not cool. Education is.', 67882, 0), (434638, '''Cyberspace'' as a term is sort of over. It''s over in the way that, after a certain time, people stopped using the suffix ''-electro'' to make things cool, because everything was electrical. ''Electro'' was all over the early 20th century, and now it''s gone. I think ''cyber'' is sort of the same way.', 9661, 0), (434639, 'My advice to young people wanting to make music and to be in this industry is to really spend your time making music. Make so much music you have no friends. Make music. Figure out what it is you love, and... because if you''re making cool art, then everything else will fall into line.', 14534, 0), (434640, 'Growing up in a cold place, in Southern Ontario, Woolrich was a brand of choice for us because it was always warm and comfortable. The parka with the fur on it was standard fare for us. It''s extraordinary that they have kept up with the times. Beyond the parka, they have changed, and they have some pretty hip, cool items which I wear.', 67950, 0), (434641, 'Entrepreneurship is seen as if you''re in Silicon Valley or New York City and starting an app business or a social-media business, which is cool. But what we really have to focus on is people who make things, and how can we fund them, and how can we encourage people to stay in their community and make a difference in their community.', 66705, 0), (434642, 'We believe it is bad or dangerous to be carried away by our emotions. We admire the person who is cool, who acts without feeling.', 14546, 0), (434643, 'I don''t like to say ''dork'' and ''nerd'' and things like that because I think that everyone is cool in their own right.', 69297, 0), (434644, 'Thom Browne, Michael Bastian... all these people that I love, when I finally get to meet them, I''m like, ''You''re a cool guy!''', 69298, 0), (434645, 'I have this obsession with really cool, old books.', 69299, 0), (434646, 'Asking Siri where the nearest sushi bar is - that''s not interesting. What''s interesting is asking your phone where one of your friends have last had dinner in the neighborhood, or having it recommend a cool paella place in Barcelona because it knows you eat paella all the time at home.', 69300, 0), (434647, 'In 2007, I hit 50 home runs. That was pretty cool. I never thought I''d be able to do that. At the time, I didn''t even think it was that big of a deal for some reason. But now, looking back, I realize it was pretty cool.', 69301, 0), (434648, 'Living in New Zealand, it''s like a different world - it is a different world. It''s very, very cool.', 69302, 0), (434649, 'Growing up, I didn''t get the talk of ''Make sure boys take you on a date and treat you right.'' So I was the girl who wasn''t dating and would just text. I dated these guys who didn''t have jobs, and I would always be paying. At one point, I remember looking in the mirror and thinking, ''You''re too pretty and cool to be treated like this.''', 69303, 0), (434650, 'I am the ''Cosmic Dancer'' who dances his way out of the womb and into the tomb on ''Electric Warrior.'' I''m not frightened to get up there and groove about in front of six million people on TV because it doesn''t look cool. That''s the way I would do it at home.', 7292, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434651, 'I have got prostate cancer, and I have to keep monitoring that. It''s no problem, it''s under control and I''m very cool about it, but other people are dying from it.', 67001, 0), (434652, 'The only other thing I can really remember wanting to do besides acting was a gas station attendant. At the time, that seemed like a great job - wash the windows, pump the gas - it looks so cool coming home with black hands. There''s a natural transition, from wanting to be a gas station attendant to being an actor, right?', 51499, 0), (434653, 'The reason it has taken so long for the robotics industry to move forward is because people keep trying to make something that is cool but difficult to achieve rather than trying to find solutions to actual human problems. Technology can be extremely expensive if you don''t focus.', 69270, 0), (434654, 'To me, Sid Vicious is cool. Super chill.', 19593, 0), (434655, 'I''m cool with my body, I love my body. I wouldn''t trade it for no other body.', 59506, 0), (434656, 'Being on a lunchbox was awesome, and being on a thermos was pretty cool, too.', 69304, 0), (434657, 'Rey is so strong. She''s cool and smart and she can look after herself. Young girls can look at her and know that they can wear trousers if they want to. That they don''t have to show off their bodies.', 67358, 0), (434658, 'I''ve done so much travelling in the past few years, and when you travel, you realise that we do actually have a cool, clean look in Scandinavia - it''s not just Denmark - which I think brings peace if you have it in your home.', 69305, 0), (434659, 'Getting to share the stories in my head with other people and have them enjoy those stories, and having them come to see my characters as real. That''s so cool.', 23526, 0), (434660, 'The really cool thing about festivals is that you''re getting to play in front of a whole lot of people who have never heard of us before. That''s exciting. At the same time, it''s a little bit of a challenge to capture the attention of people who have already seen a lot of bands.', 22928, 0), (434661, 'Technology is cool, but you''ve got to use it as opposed to letting it use you.', 12819, 0), (434662, 'I write poems, I meditate. I don''t live up to people''s expectations. I don''t do the conventional cool things - I know I am the coolest person.', 67017, 0), (434663, 'Isn''t it crazy to think that we''ve explored space more than we have explored the depths of our ocean? That just fires up my imagination about potential sea monsters and cool creatures, that kind of stuff.', 69246, 0), (434664, 'When you''re playing music through the streets of London at 2 o''clock in the morning, there''s something so cool and magical about that. It takes you to a special place very quickly.', 60126, 0), (434665, 'There''s no idea or concept in comedy you could do that hasn''t been attacked from some angle. But if you start leaving punchlines out so you''ll look cool, I don''t get that. But I don''t watch standup anyway, so I don''t know what they''re doing.', 1252, 0), (434666, 'I think, for the first time, people are starting to say, ''That''s Sterling K. Brown,'' which is cool, which is uncharted territory for your boy. It''s nice to be called by your name when you''re not in character.', 69306, 0), (434667, 'Anything I get to wear to the Met Ball is huge. I''m not a fashion girl, so it''s cool to be dolled up and have those diamonds where they send armed guards with you.', 67832, 0), (434668, 'My best friend was really cool, and she went to a youth theatre in Paisley, so I thought maybe that''s the way to do it. I went along, and I immediately found something I was passionate about and really enjoyed.', 69307, 0), (434669, 'I have to stay calm, cool, and collected.', 69308, 0), (434670, 'The films that have influenced me most are: ''The Hustler'', ''Badlands'', ''Hud'', ''Tender Mercies'', ''Cool Hand Luke'', ''A Perfect World'', and ''Laurence of Arabia''. I also really like ''Fletch''. I feel like all of these films reached an honest place in regard to the human condition while also stringing together really entertaining stories.', 68441, 0), (434671, 'It wasn''t like I wanted to be the next Marc Andreessen, but it would be cool to be in the same place.', 69309, 0), (434672, 'People expect you to be doing something cool all the time. In a normal life, that''s not happening!', 69310, 0), (434673, 'My aspiration isn''t to be famous; it''s to design clothes. If that gets me attention at the end of the day, cool.', 69311, 0), (434674, 'My brother''s my best friend, without a doubt. Me and my big sister get along so well. She moved to East London, though, so points off, but she''s wicked. And then my little sister is a little genius. She''s super talented and such a great person, always been far more mature and cool than me.', 67059, 0), (434675, 'When the NBA adopted their uniform that they had to wear, I thought that was very interesting. And you see the way NBA players dress: It''s very cool.', 66949, 0), (434676, 'At the end of the day, we all know what the Jordan logo means, and you can''t take anything away from that. But it''s pretty cool to have my own logo on a Jordan shoe.', 69312, 0), (434677, 'I am young, and I am cool, and I want to wear cool clothes!', 69313, 0), (434678, 'One of the reasons I''m excited by what visionary Elon Musk has done with the Tesla is to show that you can reduce global warming and drive a powerful, fun car. A cool car helps make a cooler planet.', 45749, 0), (434679, 'It''s just cool to witness talent.', 69314, 0), (434680, 'When you''re growing up, I think there''s this idea that the coolest people are the ones who are really rude and feverish. But I''ve come to realize that isn''t cool.', 60194, 0), (434681, 'I''m just trying to work out a way to be a singer and to create cool content. I''m willing to do that as an entertainer. But I''m not willing to give up my actual self.', 68242, 0), (434682, 'I wasn''t the cool kid in school, but I wasn''t the lame one. I knew I wasn''t cool, so I called myself lame, and that''s what made me cool in front of the cool kids.', 69315, 0), (434683, 'I laugh at what I used to think was cool when I was growing up. In all seriousness, I thought having braces was cool.', 69076, 0), (434684, 'I think the whole thing, boy band, it''s a little bit of a dirty word. They say it''s not a good thing to be in a boy band. We want to change that. We want to make the boy band cool. It''s not just about dancing and dressing the same.', 29969, 0), (434685, 'And of course I''ve got kids of my own now, and they love me being in the Harry Potter films. I''m now part of a phenomenon. You become incredibly cool to your kids, and you get a young fan base. So you became the cool dad at school. You''re suddenly hip.', 3625, 0), (434686, 'I used to be a cool chick but I''m not anymore.', 13881, 0), (434687, 'As a kid, I did want to be an old-timer, since they were the ones with the big stories and the cool clothes. I wanted to go there. Now, I guess I want to bring that with me and go back in time.', 2201, 0), (434688, 'Long intros are cool because there''s a little bit of anticipation, you know?', 36193, 0), (434689, 'It''s cool to be recognised by your peers.', 22945, 0), (434690, 'It''s pretty cool to see how far music can take you.', 66563, 0), (434691, 'I was the kid growing up who would play with G.I. Joes in a pink dress and then run off to play with my Barbies. It doesn''t mean that I''m less girly, it just means that I have this other side of me. It''s kinda cool to be a little bit of both, I think.', 69086, 0), (434692, 'Music''s been with me from the get-go. It was always around me as a kid. Dad got me my first guitar when I was 11 and, at school, if you wanted to be cool you had to be in a band.', 69017, 0), (434693, 'I think part of picking where you live in New York is accepting who you are. Really looking at yourself and going, ''Yeah, I''m not cool enough for the West Village.''', 1219, 0), (434694, 'It''s very important to enjoy time alone with yourself and just existing, because existence is kind of cool.', 69316, 0), (434695, 'What''s cool about Spider-Man is that it''s everybody - anyone, you put on the suit, anyone believes that you''re Spider-Man. That''s what''s charming about the character. He''s anyone. He''s a huge nerd that ends up being this huge superhero.', 69317, 0), (434696, 'Being cool is when you win, you don''t get too happy; and when you lose, you don''t get too mad.', 11834, 0), (434697, 'I was feeling like a real misfit in middle school, but when I saw ''Wicked,'' it made me feel really cool for being different... and you can carve that in stone!', 69318, 0), (434698, 'Photographing friends means that there''s a spontaneity to the images. I have a lot of love for my friends and family, and I love taking cool pictures of them.', 68894, 0), (434699, 'The concept of the robot encapsulates both aspects of technology. On one hand it''s cool, it''s fun, it''s healthy, it''s sexy, it''s stylish. On the other hand it''s terrifying, it''s alienating, it''s addictive, and it''s scary. That has been the subject of much science-fiction literature.', 69319, 0), (434700, 'It''s pretty cool I''m known for FIFA. If you think of KSI, people instantly think, ''Ah, that FIFA YouTuber.'' I didn''t think I would be up there as the ambassador of FIFA on YouTube, but I''ll take it.', 69320, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434701, 'I never panic when I get a wasp at my ear. As soon as you strike out, they''ll sting you. So just stay cool.', 67683, 0), (434702, 'At a young age, it is hard to be different from the crowd. I want to encourage young girls that it is cool to be different. Young women should be pleased they have something unique and make the most of their talent.', 69321, 0), (434703, 'There are some parts of my life that are wonderful, and it''s amazing to get to go to cool events and award shows and things like that, but I think the outside perception is that your life just changes overnight and you wear Dolce and Gabanna suits and drive a Mercedes. But life''s just not like that.', 68281, 0), (434704, 'Pluto is still active four and a half billion years into its history. It was expected that small planets like Pluto would cool off long ago and not still be showing geological activity. Pluto is, in fact, showing numerous examples of geological activity on a massive scale across the planet.', 66716, 0), (434705, 'I do value the respect I get from my contemporaries, but to have Oasis cover my song, to have Puff Daddy cover a song, to have Goldie come along to my gigs - that''s where my ego is at. To have my fellow musicians like what I do, that''s very cool.', 1232, 0), (434706, 'I loved the world of roller derby because I thought it was such an empowering metaphor, that you get out there and do it. It''s such a rocker, athletic, capable, cool exhibitionist sport; it''s about this great sort of camaraderie.', 292, 0), (434707, 'There''s something about girls together, uniting, that I just thought was cool.', 60194, 0), (434708, 'I''ve always loved Jennifer Lopez, and I think, as an entertainer, she is a great example of a strong woman that is also very levelheaded and cool and produces her own content.', 67850, 0), (434709, 'When I was a child, it was cool to be a scientist.', 1821, 0), (434710, 'I look at other people my age in this industry, other famous people my age, and they''ve just got famous friends. Which is cool, but I love being normal and just chilling at mine.', 21196, 0), (434711, 'A powerful person is equally cool with their flaws and things that aren''t powerful about them at all.', 69322, 0), (434712, 'What is cool today is not going to be cool tomorrow, and what wasn''t cool yesterday is going to be cool tomorrow.', 68211, 0), (434713, 'I enjoy fashion photography and textiles, that whole aspect of it. As more of an art form, I like Proenza Schouler. Those guys are really cool because they seem to have an interesting approach to it all.', 69323, 0), (434714, 'I always say, ''If it looks good on a T-shirt, it would probably be a pretty cool title or cool song.''', 67360, 0), (434715, 'The challenge is to stay cool enough to handle the pressure in the moment so that you can succeed in the future.', 69324, 0), (434716, 'The softest thing I''ve ever heard are the wind chimes in my backyard. They are soft and cool and mellow.', 68262, 0), (434717, 'I used to love to draw. I didn''t want to go to art class because I felt that would be too corny when I was young, but architectural drafting was the cool thing to do because there was more precision. It taught me a lot about building and structures and doorways and frames and windowsills.', 26404, 0), (434718, 'I don''t mind The Boss. I think he''s an honest guy. I have some of his records, not all of them. I''ve met a couple of the E-Street guys, and they seem really cool.', 68, 0), (434719, 'In Israel, there''s a lot to learn from anyone, because to live there you''ve got to deal with the truth. Things happen real fast. Your day goes from cool to catastrophic in one second. Israelis know that the cafe you''re in could blow up, or the shopping mall, and they rock that.', 68, 0), (434720, 'America was cool with Saddam Hussein when he was killing Iranians.', 68, 0), (434721, 'I wonder what it''s like to be from a state that is spread across a few islands way out in the Pacific Ocean, only added to the United States in 1959. Not only that but to be the birthplace of America''s first black president? Pretty cool, I bet.', 68, 0), (434722, 'Most Americans are very cool people.', 68, 0), (434723, 'I get along with Australians really well. Everyone''s usually really cool, and it''s always a drag to leave.', 68, 0), (434724, 'I hate painting with a broad brush, but I think the birther thing, at its root, is racist. The guy was born in Hawaii. A black guy is president. It''s cool. Get over it. Just deal with it. There''s nothing you could show these birther people that would shut them up.', 68, 0), (434725, 'Imagine a 15-year-old kid saying, ''I have two moms - it''s cool.'' I don''t fear that at all.', 68, 0), (434726, 'I am not immune to the lure of a signed record, flier or set list. The fact that your music heroes potentially had, in their own hands, the record you now have in yours is kind of cool. When the musician has departed, it can give the thing a unique power.', 68, 0), (434727, 'Horses and horsepower alike are about status and being cool.', 10731, 0), (434728, 'I don''t ever feel like the cool kid at the party, ever. It''s like, ''Smile and be nice to everybody, because you were not invited to be here.''', 100, 0), (434729, 'I think who you are in school really sticks with you. I don''t ever feel like the cool kid at the party, ever. It''s like, ''Smile and be nice to everybody, because you were not invited to be here.''', 100, 0), (434730, 'It never mattered to me that people in school didn''t think that country music was cool, and they made fun of me for it - though it did matter to me that I was not wearing the clothes that everybody was wearing at that moment. But at some point, I was just like, ''I like wearing sundresses and cowboy boots.''', 100, 0), (434731, 'When I''m 40 and nobody wants to see me in a sparkly dress anymore, I''ll be like: ''Cool, I''ll just go in the studio and write songs for kids.''', 100, 0), (434732, 'If someone has a really great boyfriend or career, I think, it''s cool that happens.', 100, 0), (434733, 'One of the biggest challenges we have, folks, is making liberty and freedom cool.', 17531, 0), (434734, 'The advent of cellphones may, in the end, be no more relevant than the ability of laptops to change our written documents into ones using cool new fonts.', 1002, 0), (434735, 'I would like to fly in space. Absolutely. That would be cool. I used to just do personally risky things, but now I''ve got kids and responsibilities, so I can''t be my own test pilot. That wouldn''t be a good idea. But I definitely want to fly as soon as it''s a sensible thing to do.', 10864, 0), (434736, 'So there''s nothing more provocative than taking a genre that everybody who''s cool hates - and then making it cool.', 47, 0), (434737, 'The thing is, it''s not uncool to worry about people who seem like they''re going on the wrong path. There''s nothing cool about being self-destructive.', 1883, 0), (434738, 'It''s not uncool to worry about people who seem like they''re going on the wrong path. There''s nothing cool about being self-destructive.', 1883, 0), (434739, 'That''s one of the cool things about fame. You have an affect on society and where it goes.', 67519, 0), (434740, 'I have a cycle that is not particularly cool, but it''s a cycle: trash myself to reward myself.', 67519, 0), (434741, 'My mother and my father were very nurturing and wonderful examples of how to live your life. I really had a cool foundation.', 67519, 0), (434742, 'I grew up not really having anything, so the idea that I can take care of my family and my friends now is a really cool bonus.', 746, 0), (434743, 'I don''t like the ironic tone that our pop culture, in the world, has taken. Everything is ''ironic.'' Everything is ''cool.''', 60783, 0), (434744, 'You make yourself broad. You make yourself appealing. ''Hey, y''all, I''m cool with everybody.'' That''s my message.', 44935, 0), (434745, 'I''m not cool enough to hang out with any rock stars. Jay-Z doesn''t come over to my house. I don''t hang out with Ted Nugent.', 66992, 0), (434746, 'London Fashion Week isn''t the most organised, but I don''t mind that. It''s such an exciting place - it''s small and cool.', 67000, 0), (434747, 'When I was a kid, maybe 11, I remember saying, ''When I grow up I wanna have enough money to buy a really cool car, because I won''t.''', 1099, 0), (434748, 'I am not a fan of referencing your own work when it''s in a different universe than what you''re doing. That, to me, is a wink at the audience, and winking isn''t actually cool when you''re not, like, 10.', 1099, 0), (434749, 'It''s only recently women got to be action heroes on TV. Progress is slow, and often non-existent. There''s plenty of cool comics with female characters... But all it takes is one Catwoman to set the cause back a decade.', 1099, 0), (434750, 'I was probably cool around the end of 2002.', 13073, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434751, 'I don''t like ''cool telly.''', 13073, 0), (434752, 'I''m not quite as cool as I would like to be, really.', 67001, 0), (434753, 'My friends are people who like building cool stuff. We always have this joke about people who want to just start companies without making something valuable. There''s a lot of that in Silicon Valley.', 5553, 0), (434754, 'A lot of people are focused on taking over the world or doing the biggest thing and getting the most users. I think part of making a difference and doing something cool is focusing intensely.', 5553, 0), (434755, 'My goal was never to make Facebook cool. I am not a cool person.', 5553, 0), (434756, '''Fast and Furious'' is the only franchise that I''ve directed that I did not create from scratch. So it definitely was an eye-opening experience for me coming to that world. I had to be respectful of the roles that had been established by the filmmakers before me, and I was cool with that.', 69246, 0), (434757, 'My low-budget films, more than anything, taught me that you''ve got to create cool, likable characters and great stories because, if you don''t, it doesn''t matter how cool it might look - no one is going to care about it.', 69246, 0), (434758, 'I always say, what is cool for me with ''The Conjuring'', is it''s not just another scary set piece or another scary case; it''s more about what I can do with the characters of Ed and Lorraine Warren.', 69246, 0), (434759, 'There''s something very cool about that indie spirit that I try to hang on to even now with the bigger films that I''m working on.', 69246, 0), (434760, 'I grew up loving X-Men, Spider-Man and Batman. Those are obviously the key big ones, but there''s always something kind of cool about Aquaman still, the idea of creating a huge world that is on our planet.', 69246, 0), (434761, 'I won''t do things for money. I can''t. So I''ll hold out and say, in my mind, ''There''s a really cool diner down the street from my house. They make really good pancakes; I''d be happy doing that.''', 46525, 0), (434762, 'The cool thing about designers is they have very specific points of view, and because my inspiration is always changing, it''s easy to go, ''This feels right.'' But just because I wear fancy dresses on weekends doesn''t mean in my heart of hearts I''m not a jeans and T-shirt person.', 46525, 0), (434763, 'I have snakes, three sharks, moray eels, piranhas, five scorpions and a bird spider. All of them are predators. They are dangerous but it''s cool to have strong and powerful pets.', 68238, 0), (434764, 'Cool is the enemy of funny. You can''t be cool and be funny at the same time. Only Eddie Murphy could do that.', 68238, 0), (434765, 'The truth is - I found myself doing these huge action-adventure movies, and um, and which are cool man. And I really love doing them. And thankfully I haven''t had too much dialogue, because if I had I would have really made a mess of it. You know what I mean?', 68239, 0), (434766, 'Elves are cool, man.', 68239, 0), (434767, 'I wondered how they would top the Pirates and skeletons and moonlight, because that''s a pretty cool concept.', 68239, 0), (434768, 'I''m trying to mix the cool, independent stuff with the big stuff, but it''s been difficult finding the right roles. It''s been an interesting ride as far as my career pendulum is concerned.', 68239, 0), (434769, 'Steve McQueen is my style hero. He''s just cool, isn''t he?', 68239, 0), (434770, 'When I realized that if I was an actor, I could be any character I wanted instead of just one particular, I was like, ''Wow, that''s cool.''', 68239, 0), (434771, 'I used to ride motorbikes and drive cars like everything was a racetrack it was ridiculous. It wasn''t because I thought it was cool it was just because I loved living on the edge. But I''ve chilled. ', 68239, 0), (434772, 'The nerds are the ones that make the films and do loads of other really cool stuff in their life.', 1593, 0), (434773, 'I''ve never been one of the cool people at school, but then again, I don''t get the people who are cool. It''s not that I don''t like them, it''s just that they don''t interest me.', 1593, 0), (434774, 'I met Elijah Wood once, I met Peter Jackson, I met Orlando Bloom, and they''re all really cool.', 1593, 0), (434775, 'A part of me wants to sort of try and sound cool and feed this myth that I''m some sort of glamorous lothario, but I was raised by women - my mother and her mother and my aunts - and as a result, most of my friends have always been women.', 67002, 0), (434776, 'I recently discovered Artkive, a wonderful app that allows you to archive your child''s artwork and create cool gifts like photo albums, mugs, mousepads, etc. It''s very easy to use, and since Arabella is such a talented artist, I''m a pro!', 26172, 0), (434777, 'If you could drive straight down, into a tunnel bored through the crust of the planet, you''d hit this molten mess in about an hour. It''s called the asthenosphere - a sluggish sea, several hundred miles thick, on which floats the Earth''s cool epidermis - the so-called tectonic plates.', 13839, 0), (434778, 'Plate tectonics is not all havoc and destruction. The slow movement of continents and ocean floors recycles carbon dioxide dissolved in the oceans back into the atmosphere. Without this slow speed carbon cycle, Earth''s temperatures would cool dozens of degrees below your comfort zone.', 13839, 0), (434779, 'Gwen Stefani''s style and flow I just love. She is so cool to me!', 68240, 0), (434780, 'I''d love to be the female Kanye. I think he''s so cool and effortless.', 68240, 0), (434781, 'They''re very, uh, you know, I don''t come from the suburbs and a jolly, Disney type of lifestyle. I come from something totally different. And they''re cool and bare minimum so it''s not always a money issue for me.', 66795, 0), (434782, 'What''s cool is when you''re able to give your audience imagination and you don''t have to cage them in like animals.', 66795, 0), (434783, 'I''m a video game fan, and I always thought it would be cool to be able to control a character.', 66795, 0), (434784, 'If people could walk around in suits of energy, that would be cool. Other than that, I don''t think men should wear spandex.', 38496, 0), (434785, 'Ngila Dixon is such an incredible costume designer. She''s such a cool, stylish woman. She has such an understanding of character.', 38496, 0), (434786, 'So, it''s cool that, yes, Hal Jordan is a superhero, but my character is a real-world hero in her own life.', 38496, 0), (434787, 'I still, at hotel rooms, I do this one sort of not-so-cool thing: continually shoving my room service tray in front of someone else''s door. Because I don''t want the remnants. I don''t want to be caught, like, being like the pig that I was at two in the morning.', 292, 0), (434788, 'I remember being on film sets when I was younger, and only men got to do the cool action movies. So I thought, ''Maybe I''ll get to produce one day and get to do cool stuff, too,'' which is what happened when we did ''Charlie''s Angels''.', 292, 0), (434789, 'My mother used to dress rather risque when I was a kid, and that sort of shocked me. I always thought moms were supposed to wear cardigans and flats, but she was in leather bracelets and minidresses. In hindsight, it was pretty cool, but I''m probably more conservative because of it.', 292, 0), (434790, 'It took being famous to make me cool, which, by the way, I never forgot.', 12642, 0), (434791, 'People want to go out and travel around and meet cool people. I could just go live in Vermont, but is that what I really want?', 66949, 0), (434792, 'I love the idea of real-life experiences finding their way into fiction. I think that''s really cool.', 67004, 0), (434793, 'Someone like Vincent Price or somebody like Christopher Lee, they never won an award, and it doesn''t matter. They''re cool.', 67437, 0), (434794, 'Mike Myers as Austin Powers makes me laugh - that was genius - and Daffy Duck makes me laugh, but I like odd behavior. I don''t like hip dialogue and one-liners and all that sort of cool, sophomoric comedy. It''s just not for me.', 67437, 0), (434795, 'In the hot summer months, popsicles are a perfect way to cool down while enjoying a delicious, fruity treat. Frozen, refreshing, mouth-friendly candy on a stick cannot get any better... or can it?', 32425, 0), (434796, 'It''s cool cause my sister is older than me and we went to the same high school, so by the time I got to high school, I got the lowdown on all the teachers and everything.', 22856, 0), (434797, 'I went to Northwestern because I had gone to a really nontraditional high school. I was like, ''It''d be cool to have a traditional college experience.'' Then I was like, ''Oh, but none of these people understand what''s cool about me. My specialness is not appreciated in this place.''', 22856, 0), (434798, 'Growing up in Hollywood meant there were a lot of film stars'' kids at my school - but no conspicuous wealth. It wasn''t cool to show off that you had money.', 22856, 0), (434799, 'But being on location and shooting, whether its in Puerto Rico or Atlanta, it always reminds me of how really cool my job can be. Interacting with the fans is one of the best parts of it.', 11331, 0), (434800, '''Be Cool'' was a defining movie for me.', 11331, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434801, 'If you''re going to walk out of the house in jeans and T-shirt, what can you do to make that interesting? Is it putting on a bright-colored pair of high-tops or a cool leather jacket?', 69298, 0), (434802, 'The forties are very cool and very pastoral. The fifties look like they''re pastoral, and then you get a bit more turbulence.', 67399, 0), (434803, 'Susanne Bier''s work I''ve always really enjoyed. She''s just such a great filmmaker; she''s very cool and very sexy - that always helps, too.', 67399, 0), (434804, 'I love ''Maxim,'' actually. It''s very cool.', 67399, 0), (434805, 'Crunches are much more effective than regular sit-ups because they specifically target your upper abdominal muscles rather than your hip muscles. If you''re not used to them, they can cause soreness a day or two later, but it''s a ''cool'' soreness. A badge of honor.', 35699, 0), (434806, 'I''ve always believed in good music over bad music. I believe in two sorts of musics. And the lines that separate us, I don''t believe in that. That''s for people who need to easily define what they''re hearing. Me, I''m cool with everything and anything I''m hearing that''s music. It comes under one definition for me.', 8650, 0), (434807, 'You make your first album, you make some money, and you feel like you still have to show face, like ''I still go to the projects.'' I''m like, why? Your job is to inspire people from your neighborhood to get out. You grew up there. What makes you think it''s so cool?', 8650, 0), (434808, 'Growing up, politics never trickled down to the areas we come from. But people from Obama''s camp, and Obama himself, reached out to me and asked for my help on the campaign. We''ve sat and had dinner, and we''ve spoken on the phone. He''s a very sharp guy. Very charming. Very cool.', 8650, 0), (434809, 'No one dislikes LL Cool J. If you meet LL Cool J, you fall in love with LL Cool J. LL and I had mutual friends, and he and I had always talked about doing something. My fans know LL''s music. And I love him - we''re blood brothers at this point. We''ve been through the fire together. I know no finer person.', 34097, 0), (434810, 'The artists who stick around for a while are the ones who go, ''Oh, that''s cool, never thought of that. Ought to do that.''', 34097, 0), (434811, 'Obama can''t change his cool disposition, though it would be nice if he lost the vaguely grudging air he gives off that problems of management get in the way of ideas.', 18085, 0), (434812, 'The reason why I am proud of my part in the punk movement is that I think it really did implant a message that was already there. The hippies told it to me, but punk made it something cool for people to stand up for, which is that we do not believe government, that we are against government.', 13967, 0), (434813, 'I think big brows are pretty cool.', 60194, 0), (434814, 'I think it''s cool to be a rock star I don''t think there are many. There aren''t many who speak out and take risks. And I think that''s important. ', 60194, 0), (434815, 'I think the best people are the ones who are just as nice and fun. This is really cheesy, but you only have one life - why spend most of it pretending to be cool?', 60194, 0), (434816, 'I''m lucky I have really cool parents.', 60194, 0), (434817, 'I was never the cool kid in school, and loads of people told me that I was weird, that I dressed uncool and did uncool things, that I was too nice, too happy.', 60194, 0), (434818, 'I''ve always wanted to write pop music. I never wanted to be cool or make a hipster record.', 60194, 0), (434819, 'I never set out to be a cult cool artist. I always made music that I thought was pop.', 60194, 0), (434820, 'I used to worry about being cool. Now I realize that I genuinely don''t care.', 60194, 0), (434821, 'Sometimes I feel like I was born in the wrong year - I think it would have been cool to be alive in the ''60s.', 60194, 0), (434822, 'I''ve passed up on many a thing that could have made me a big artist or something. Like, I was offered a feature on a Christina Aguilera song and I turned it down. It just wasn''t right. She''s cool, but it just wasn''t right.', 60194, 0), (434823, 'Being cool, having a ''cool'' energy is just not attractive to me.', 793, 0), (434824, 'My mom was really cool.', 62003, 0), (434825, 'There are people out there who are older who are cool. I want that.', 4019, 0), (434826, 'At my age, I''m not trying to score cool points. I''m just excited when I can speak to younger members of our audience in the WWE. I just get to be a superhero to kids, but I''m not trying to be on the cutting edge of style or anything like that. Once you reach that point of deprivation, you don''t mind it.', 38715, 0), (434827, 'Blood is one of the things that made fights cool. Like, you knew it had gotten serious. I understand why we don''t do it anymore.', 38715, 0), (434828, 'I really, really, really love my job, so it''s not like I''m trying to quit wrestling to do movies. They just all seemed like cool things to do. I mean, I''d love to be the bad guy in an action movie because then people would get to see another side of me they don''t get to see.', 38715, 0), (434829, 'That''s how I grew up - it wasn''t cool to not have a good system.', 33596, 0), (434830, 'I always wanted to be where the cool was because I didn''t think I was cool. But music was cool.', 33596, 0), (434831, 'I can''t learn in school, but I can learn from somebody who I think is cool and great.', 33596, 0), (434832, 'I knew in my heart that I wasn''t cool, but I figured I could at least be cool by association.', 33596, 0), (434833, 'I follow cool. When I went up to see Steve Jobs, I said, ''The party''s at this guy''s house.''', 33596, 0), (434834, 'Seeing young people caring about sound again and realizing that it''s not cool to not have good sound, that means a lot.', 33596, 0), (434835, 'I have a satellite radio show called ''The Legends of Reggae.'' It''s a cool way to branch out and do other things. I''m paying respect to the legends of reggae.', 13964, 0), (434836, 'My father and I had a really good relationship. We''re cool. I am not trying to outdo him or anything like that.', 13964, 0), (434837, 'I suppose the only thing at 50 you can really start to look forward to is just total irresponsibility. As you get older, you can just sit in a chair, wear anything you want, you know you can walk down; old people dress cool. You know they wear sweatpants. The elderly have it down.', 148, 0), (434838, 'iTunes kind of feels like Sam Goody to me. I don''t feel cool when I go there. I''m tired of seeing John Mayer''s face pop up.', 60178, 0), (434839, '''Yeezus,'' I really love it. I think the sound of it is cool.', 60178, 0), (434840, 'When your culture comes from watching TV every day, you''re bombarded with images of things that seem cool, places that seem interesting, people who have jobs and careers and opportunities. None of that happened where I was. You''re almost taught to realize it''s not for you.', 60178, 0), (434841, 'A good president needs a big comfort zone. He should be able to treat enemies as opportunities, appear authentic in joy and grief, stay cool under the hot lights.', 36805, 0), (434842, 'I loved animation and cartoons, even when it was not cool when you were in high school. I raced home to see the Bugs Bunny cartoons.', 68139, 0), (434843, 'I love Japan. I love the collision of the modern and ancient worlds coming together in that place. It''s so high-tech and cool.', 68139, 0), (434844, 'Fortunately for me, I''m married to an amazing woman - Nancy Lasseter - who is wise enough not to let me buy every car I want. If I was single, I would be living in a very small apartment and renting a warehouse full of cool cars.', 68139, 0), (434845, 'Nowadays, the truth is, I think a lot of the newer generation of action stars usually are pretty self-deprecating and cool. I mean, Dwayne Johnson is a great example.', 23202, 0), (434846, 'McCain is the kid who was really cool in middle school but never got high school game and people are sick of him acting like he''s still popular.', 23202, 0), (434847, 'When I think of the definition of cool and when I look at people, John Travolta is really the definition of cool because, not only is he great in all his movies, but, as a person, he''s just really cool.', 67850, 0), (434848, 'My real last name is Flores, and Milian is actually my mom''s maiden name. So it''s not made up, which is cool; it runs in the family. And it actually worked out better for my career to have the last name Milian, because Flores kept me in a little box, and no one really associated me with the last name Flores.', 67850, 0), (434849, 'I had a really great performance with Steven Tyler in the movie ''Be Cool.'' I performed ''Cryin'','' so we recorded the song beforehand. But I didn''t get to meet him until I hit the stage with him, and we had a live performance with 30,000 people in the audience, and that was for the movie.', 67850, 0), (434850, 'In the end, the whole Internet thing kills me, because you can use it as a positive thing or you can read into all the negativity. And I think you''ve gotta put out positive energy, put out cool viral stuff, and then just stay out of people''s opinions.', 1197, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434851, 'I just think if I can go from being a homeless kid with a dream of being in the biggest band in the world and making that happen, I can do a lot of other cool stuff, too.', 1197, 0), (434852, 'If your album sells, that''s cool, more people find out about you, more people get turned on to what we''re really about-which is a live rock and roll band.', 1197, 0), (434853, 'Reflecting back, we all make mistakes; we all go through our stuff - relationships, financial, all kinds of stuff - and if you can grow from that and pass that message on, it''s a pretty cool thing.', 1197, 0), (434854, 'It''s really cool to know that there are so many people out there that are attached to me or projects that I''ve done to really feel that it''s a personal relationship.', 1197, 0), (434855, 'Nothing that Robert Plant does will ever equal Led Zeppelin, but that doesn''t mean he''s going to stop being creative. Jimmy Page has so many incredibly cool projects, but it''s not Led Zeppelin; there will only ever be one Led Zeppelin.', 1197, 0), (434856, 'After a while, you just want transportation, and things like cool cars or motorcycles are all about getting attention. I get all the attention I could ever need, so I kind of like being in a minivan and people not paying so much attention to me.', 7961, 0), (434857, 'I just like short hair on women I think it''s cool. ', 69325, 0), (434858, 'What a cool job to be part of - whether it''s doing lighting or acting or serving food on set. You''re part of telling a story that hopefully has an essential component, and that''s super exciting to me.', 68913, 0), (434859, 'I didn''t want to be a genius! That ain''t cool.', 69257, 0), (434860, 'Every day I am being told to sign up for Tumblr, Yammer, Friendfeed, Plaxo, Last.fm, ping.fm or the hot social-media tool du jour that happened to get mentioned on Mashable.com. It is like a social-media arms race. Each one of these new tools is like a cool new night club. Hot today, gone tomorrow, replaced with something else.', 67775, 0), (434861, 'An Oklahoma girl like me wouldn''t even know how to be a diva. I''m just a person who has a cool job. I love to be at home. I rarely go to clubs... and I always wear underwear! I just know I''d fall down, and that''s not for everyone to see.', 452, 0), (434862, 'I like John McCain, or he seems like a cool guy in a lot of ways. I don''t agree with a lot of his policies, but he still seems like a cool guy.', 63558, 0), (434863, 'My parents were vegetarians. I''d show up at school, this giant black kid, with none of the cool clothes and a tofu sandwich and celery sticks.', 61882, 0), (434864, 'My novel, which I had started with such hope shortly after publishing my first book of stories, wouldn''t budge past the 75-page mark. Nothing I wrote past page 75 made any kind of sense. Nothing. Which would have been fine if the first 75 pages hadn''t been pretty damn cool.', 560, 0), (434865, 'If you, like, consciously think about being cool, you''re not cool. If you consciously think about being, like, different or original, you ain''t different or original.', 560, 0), (434866, 'It''s amazing: it''s so cool being from Brampton, Ontario, and being able to travel the world and being embraced by so many countries.', 68914, 0), (434867, 'It''s so cool though when I see thirty-year-old men that are coming in to watch my shows. It''s like, ''You really like my music? Like a teenage girl, you relate to it?'' It just proves how much people are alike.', 68914, 0), (434868, '''Wild Things'' is saying, ''I don''t have to belong anywhere. This is where I belong.'' It''s a place in the back of my mind that I created, and it''s cool, and I love it here.', 68914, 0), (434869, 'It doesn''t occur to me that I don''t drive a cool car until I hang out with Jon Hamm, who picks me up in what looks like a Transformer, and I think, ''Oh, that''s what movie stars are driving. I guess I''m not a movie star.''', 69326, 0), (434870, 'England is like the margin of a spring-run: near its source, always green, always cool, always moist, comparatively free from frost in winter and from drought in summer.', 1069, 0), (434871, 'Doing graphic novels is cool! It''s fun! You get to write something, and then see it visually page by page, panel by panel, working with the artist, you get to see it fleshed out.', 6719, 0), (434872, 'I listen to a lot of really old western and country music. There''s a lot of cool stuff in there... all the heartbreak of the country darkness.', 67009, 0), (434873, 'I always imagined how cool it would be to be the face of a Gap campaign!', 67009, 0), (434874, 'Sometimes you have the trends that''s not that cool. You may have certain artists portraying these trends and don''t really have that lifestyle, and then it gives off the wrong thing. And it becomes kinda corny after awhile. It''s really about keeping hip-hop original and pushing away the corniness in it.', 22894, 0), (434875, 'Once I started singing, I didn''t have to try to be cool. I was just one of the coolest guys around.', 2025, 0), (434876, 'I came from a crew, and to me, all the guys I rapped with were better than me, so I was surprised when I was the breakout one. It was definitely a cool thing.', 10195, 0), (434877, 'My mom was my main influence growing up, and Phylicia Rashad reminded me a lot of my mother, just the way she handled certain things, she was... not soft-spoken but smooth-spoken. Just very calm, cool, collected about things.', 10195, 0), (434878, 'I''m cool with myself. If I can''t have the body of Angie Bassett, so be it.', 10195, 0), (434879, 'When I''m wearing too-high heels and swaying my hips, I do that Sharon Stone kind of thing - she has the sexiest walk, a New York cool thing that throws you back.', 10195, 0), (434880, 'A guy''s biggest style mistake is definitely trying to look too cool. As long as you''ve got a good pair of jeans, a good pair of boots and a few good shirts, you''re fine.', 69302, 0), (434881, 'At that moment in time when we feel like the other, we were not the person embraced, not one of the cool kids, not in the club - when you''re that person, it makes you feel smaller, and when they persecute you as a result, that''s a difficult position to be in.', 69327, 0), (434882, 'Now, being one who lived in the era of Obama, there are so many markers of improvement made. It''s hard to be mindful of that, in the same way you''re going, ''Oh everything''s cool now!'' and it isn''t. But I try to be mindful of how much of an improvement there has been because that gives hope. You need hope. I need hope!', 69327, 0), (434883, 'The real guys that I knew were really cool people, who I played basketball with and traveled with on teams and knew their families and knew that they love their family. They just happen to do something that wasn''t all the way legal, but it was a part of their life, and you knew that they hustled.', 69327, 0), (434884, 'The first song I learned on the guitar was a Kenny Chesney song called ''What I Need to Do'' it was just an easy song to play... and it was really cool to see that come full-circle a few years later and have him record a song that I was part of. ', 67010, 0), (434885, 'All actors are my brothers and my sisters. It ain''t cool to compare or disparage them. It ain''t polite.', 68375, 0), (434886, 'It''s cool now to play golf.', 11163, 0), (434887, 'The high-spirited man may indeed die, but he will not stoop to meanness. Fire, though it may be quenched, will not become cool.', 782, 0), (434888, 'I love to add ''90s trends mixed with modern day pieces I find along my many travels. Like these cool fun hats from Europe I have. I love to collect different ones from every country. I have them from London to Brussels.', 69328, 0), (434889, '''Blade'' was amazing; I can''t imagine the character without Wesley Snipes. He just made a long, black leather trench coat look so cool.', 69328, 0), (434890, 'I''m really into kind of finding different masculine pieces and making them feminine. Like cool oxfords.', 69328, 0), (434891, 'Sometimes fashion designers will be like, ''This is what''s hot right now, and you will be cool if you wear this,'' but sometimes it''s too expensive or doesn''t look good on me or isn''t who I am, and I don''t need to just think that what you''re saying is what''s cool if I have my own identity.', 69328, 0), (434892, 'I love a cool bralette paired with a high-waisted jean, maybe with Chanel suspenders and a good platform shoe.', 69328, 0), (434893, 'I haven''t took no punishment. There''s nothing cool about taking punishment.', 67644, 0), (434894, 'Ali was a threat because he was a voice, and the people hated Ali when he was a voice, but once Ali could no longer speak and he wasn''t a voice, they loved him. Love me now. I don''t want to be loved if I could barely walk or barely talk. That''s not cool.', 67644, 0), (434895, 'It''s just a really cool deal to be a character in ''WWE 2K17.'' Whether it''s competing on Nitro or Halloween Havoc, to have me as an available character... it''s a tribute.', 67851, 0), (434896, 'I remember telling myself when I got to start having artist opportunities, ''Let yourself be a fan, because you are. The minute that you walk in a room with Carrie Underwood, and you''re too cool to freak out, you need to check yourself.'' I just let myself be a fan.', 69329, 0), (434897, 'It''s been really cool to me to watch someone like Sam Hunt, whose lyrics and roots are in country but you can hear that he listens to Drake and Justin Timberlake - and that''s OK. It allows songwriters to be more honest because it''s like, ''This is who I''m listening to.''', 69329, 0), (434898, 'It''s really cool when, in every genre of music, you can listen to a song and know what era it was from.', 69329, 0), (434899, 'When I entered high school I was an A-student, but not for long. I wanted the fancy clothes. I wanted to hang out with the guys. I went from being an A-student to a B-student to a C-student, but I didn''t care. I was getting the high fives and the low fives and the pats on the back. I was cool.', 1793, 0), (434900, 'Catty is not cool. I can''t think of anything less becoming than a man who talks about people behind their backs.', 69330, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434901, 'I''m the person friends come to when they want to find the perfect restaurant or boutique hotel on the outskirts of Paris. As opposed to scouring the Internet for a travel guide, wouldn''t you rather ask the people who are really cool who go there? That''s what I do.', 69330, 0), (434902, 'I don''t want to judge, but I''ve also met women who think it''s cool to be out or away from their baby, and I don''t get that.', 67014, 0), (434903, 'The ''90s was a decade of mundane market-consumer nothingness where there was nothing coming up from the streets you just had someone in an office deciding what was cool. ', 1425, 0), (434904, 'Because of my job, I get a lot of opportunity to grab a few days here and there in many cool cities for press commitments, magazine shoots and premieres - Barcelona, Madrid, Rome, Paris, Stockholm, New York, Berlin. I always try to get to a gallery or museum if there''s time.', 69331, 0), (434905, 'With Tinder and all these other things, there''s always this kind of illusion with infinite choices. There''s something very cool about saying, ''Oh, I actually really care about this person, and I want to commit to loving this person and being loyal to this person.'' You can''t get that from the kind of infinite multiple choices that are out there.', 28573, 0), (434906, 'My style is pretty clean, classic, and elegant, with some elements to make it a little funkier. If you see me on a normal day, I''m usually in a T-shirt and jeans, maybe with some cool sneakers, but I''m pretty basic.', 28573, 0), (434907, 'I sang ''All Of Me'' at the wedding. I sang ''Stay With You'' from my first album. And then Stevie Wonder came up and sang ''Ribbon In the Sky.'' It was impromptu... It was cool... He''s always been a friend and a mentor to me.', 28573, 0), (434908, 'With ''Transparent''. When Amazon put ''Transparent'' up, along with ''Bosch'' and a few other things, I watched them, and I thought it was an interesting exercise. I didn''t comment on them, but I was like, ''Okay, this is kind of cool.''', 26931, 0), (434909, 'We got to do a few things with President Clinton. To be invited to Washington again to play with Ashanti and all those other cool people there in front of President Bush and the rest of the world feels awesome. I''m really looking forward to going.', 69332, 0), (434910, 'I''ve been a Robert Randolph fan forever, since 2001. I just thought he was so cool; you don''t see a black kid playing the slide the way he plays. No one plays like Robert.', 69332, 0), (434911, 'I didn''t know I was cool, but I was very flattered that some of the younger comedy writers came up to talk to me at the Emmys. I found that gratifying.', 51805, 0), (434912, 'Kids all want to look cool, as if knowledge is a great burden, but they''re always looking around. They remember.', 20529, 0), (434913, 'I did find some time to go to a record store and check out ''Headstrong'' actually in the racks. It was pretty cool I never thought I''d see my own CD sitting there with everyone else''s. I made my Mom take lots of pics! ', 68247, 0), (434914, 'One of my intentions with ''Rookie'' is for the girls reading it to know that they are already cool enough and smart enough and pretty enough.', 32663, 0), (434915, 'So much about ''Rookie'' has been very organically familial among our contributors, among our readers. Yeah, if I interview someone like Lorde, who I do know outside of work - sometimes I''m just so happy; it''s so cool that this is organically, effortlessly, the warm, supportive friend vibe that we want here.', 32663, 0), (434916, 'One of my favorite things I read was John Steinbeck''s journals while he was writing ''East of Eden,'' which was so cool.', 69333, 0), (434917, 'When I was a very young actor, I cruised around in a pretty cool vehicle called the Starship Enterprise.', 45192, 0), (434918, 'I''d love to date somebody cool, fun, funny.', 7387, 0), (434919, 'I don''t know anybody as creative and unique and off the wall as Dia Frampton. She''s always asking me, ''Am I too weird?'' I just tell her, ''People don''t think you''re weird, they think you''re cool.''', 69334, 0), (434920, 'I would be lying if I said it wasn''t cool to see myself on the cover of ''Vanity Fair,'' right? It''s, like, what am I doing there? This is bizarre.', 8452, 0), (434921, 'Awkwardness gives me great comfort. I''ve never been cool, but I''ve felt cool. I''ve been in the cool place, but I wasn''t really cool - I was trying to pass for hip or cool. It''s the awkwardness that''s nice.', 19768, 0), (434922, 'When I was working on pictures with my father, there were a couple leading ladies to whom I wish I''d expressed how I felt rather than being too cool or too shy.', 23151, 0), (434923, 'I''m on the younger end of Gen X, and for me, growing up gay was not cool.', 1860, 0), (434924, 'The one person who''s disappeared out of the business is the A&R man. Because the listener at home becomes the A&R man. He''s the one who chooses what tracks he wants on the album. And that''s cool.', 20029, 0), (434925, 'I think most people think of ballerinas as kind of either as a fairytale, far-away thing that''s really not attainable, something they can''t grasp, or they think of them as European or Russian and kind of their nose up in the air. So, it''s cool for me to, like, sit with them and for them to really see themselves as me.', 50400, 0), (434926, 'For relatively modest amounts of sulfur dioxide injected into the atmosphere, you could easily cool Earth by 1% or more, if you want.', 10715, 0), (434927, 'If I say I''ve got two versions of Word - that old one from 1982 that''s perfect, with zero defects; or the new one that''s got all this cool new stuff, but there might be a few bugs in it - people always want the new one. But I wouldn''t want them to operate a plane I was on with software that happened to be the latest greatest release!', 10715, 0), (434928, 'Opening Ceremony is my number one favorite place to shop here. It''s the only place I''ll shop in New York with my son. All of the sales people are so cool; the music is great; it''s just like a big fun house, so he stays entertained.', 69212, 0), (434929, 'Even though my father was a radio comedian, it wasn''t cool to say, at a young age, ''I want to be a comedian.''', 61610, 0), (434930, 'My roots were in acting. That''s all I wanted to be. Even though my father was a radio comedian, it wasn''t cool to say, at a young age, ''I want to be a comedian.''', 61610, 0), (434931, 'I''m still a student of fashion, but I like hooking up with the people that really know how to make cool clothes.', 68919, 0), (434932, 'I really enjoy being part of the Marvel Universe. It''s a cool bunch of people to work with, and they know what they''re doing.', 67649, 0), (434933, 'You''d be surprised the type of people who are into metal when you see them. Sometimes I''m even surprised, but it''s cool. That''s the reason it''s still around.', 66906, 0), (434934, 'Back in the days, we had to work with a shoestring budget. We had a movie screen, and we''d show movie trailers on them, and then we''d rip through it and started playing. Now we have a little money to play with to do a cool stage set.', 66906, 0), (434935, 'When your car rattles when you drive, you know you are playing cool music.', 66906, 0), (434936, 'Like most people in radio - and in magic - I''m not cool. I know people who are hip, and I can feel distance between them and me.', 54808, 0), (434937, 'I started out doing production work on promos, stuff like that. I didn''t think it was cool to be working for NPR. I didn''t need anything to be cool. I just wanted something to do that would be interesting. It was fun. I didn''t think of it as anything else but fun.', 54808, 0), (434938, 'Let''s be honest. Canada wasn''t ever cool.', 23049, 0), (434939, 'I want to make pop cool again, and the only way I can do that is by being ambitious and grand.', 23049, 0), (434940, 'In high school I had a boyfriend who was super into rap, so I was into Too $hort and Wu-Tang for a little while. And my best friend''s older brother would sometimes drive us home in this pimped-out truck, and he''d play all his dirty rap music. We thought we were really cool.', 68430, 0), (434941, 'My high school didn''t have a football team; we just had like a surf team, because I grew up in Encinitas, California, which is the ultimate place where everyone skated or surfed, so it was a very different culture. It was, like, cool to be the art kid.', 67018, 0), (434942, 'I met Patti Smith, which is not Hollywood, but that really blew my mind. I love her. We were at a very small party, too, on a boat, and I totally fanned out. I told her that I loved her, and wasn''t cool at all.', 67018, 0), (434943, 'I like to buy girls shoes and jewelry. I buy stupidly expensive shoes. I got Louboutins for my mom and my girlfriend before. My mom was like, ''I can''t wear these; they''re too high.'' I was like, ''Mom, you have to try them - they''re so cool. They''re red snakeskin!'' She still wears them every so often, but she can''t walk in them.', 69335, 0), (434944, 'Being an Australian that''s been No. 1 in the world back home playing in Australia, that''s a pretty cool moment to have.', 66923, 0), (434945, 'I think it''s really cool to embrace the pain of something that may have hurt you and be able to express it through music.', 69256, 0), (434946, 'It''s one thing to really dream and have a vision and want all these cool things, but it''s a whole other thing when you actually have wisdom and understand things. Then you can truly make the best decisions.', 69256, 0), (434947, 'I think cool moments like winning a Grammy deserve a nice little party where you really soak it in and not have to work and stuff. I do remember throwing a party on that Grammy night, but it was work.', 69256, 0), (434948, 'I''m Brian a lot more than I''m Paul Walker, which is awesome. When I hear, ''Hey Paul Walker!'' my hair stands up on the back of my neck. It''s uncomfortable. But when I hear, ''It''s Brian!'' it''s cool. I like Brian.', 55738, 0), (434949, 'When you''re on the pop treadmill, you don''t always feel that cool because you have to do things to promote the record that aren''t necessarily your environment.', 69336, 0), (434950, 'I''ve always had a big personality. I was trickier as a kid. I behaved erratically instead of consistently. I would have tons of friends, and then I would have no friends. I''d be with the cool girls, then the uncool girls. I migrated from group to group because I was bored or people got bored with me. I was very intense.', 2202, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (434951, 'I love being in the studio. Expressing myself that way is really cool.', 68249, 0), (434952, 'Working with Ice Cube was so tight. He''s cool, and I really like how he does family stuff. My guy friends couldn''t believe I was chillin'' with him. Dudes love Ice Cube.', 68249, 0), (434953, 'I named my album ''So Uncool'' because it defies the ordinary: you''re different from everyone else. It''s like, being uncool makes you cool because you''re different!', 68249, 0), (434954, 'I love my bubble skirt. I wear it with a belt and my shirt tucked in. Just like a t-shirt from Nordstrom''s or something. And I wear this navy blue blazer with the sleeves crushed up. And I just feel like I''m such a cool girl when I walk out. I feel like, ''Yeah I''m cool, like a model.''', 68249, 0), (434955, 'Working with crocodiles is always amazing because they''re beautiful. They''re modern day dinosaurs, which is really cool.', 68250, 0), (434956, 'I am surprised by how not-adopted the video reply has been. What keeps other people from doing it, I think, is that they think a video comes across as ''I''m cool, look at how many e-mails I get.'' That perception doesn''t scare me, because I know who I am.', 11355, 0), (434957, 'People are more comfortable learning about wine because now they can just Google, you know, ''Soave,'' and say, ''Oh, O.K., cool.''', 11355, 0), (434958, 'When I was younger, I had a perm, and it was really big. My mom was a hairdresser, so even my dad had a perm! I looked like a poodle, but it was cool at the time.', 69264, 0), (434959, 'It was an event whenever ''CHiPs'' would come on in my house. There wasn''t a lot of Latin people being hired to star in TV shows or movies back in the day. Not only was it a fun show, there was a Latino starring in it - so we thought it was extra cool.', 68251, 0), (434960, 'Kicks to the legs, they''re not very cool. They''re brutal.', 68251, 0), (434961, 'I remember I used to think my dad was really cool working at a factory. He used to make buttons. I used to brag, ''This button here, My dad made it.'' There was this sense of pride. It''s knowing your dad is doing something cool.', 68251, 0), (434962, 'My dad is a great writer. Naturally talented, naturally charming. He embodies that back-in-the-day cool.', 22735, 0), (434963, 'When I first moved to Vail, it was like I was a little celebrity. You know, everyone knew my accomplishments. I was a young, fast teenager and making waves in the ski world. And it was really cool.', 68105, 0), (434964, 'I''m obsessed with the 1920s, everything from the style to the lifestyle. It was a really cool era.', 153, 0), (434965, 'Touring is very routine. You get to the city, you go to the hotel, you got to be at the hotel by a certain time - it''s very routine. I''m not a very structured person, so when I get some structure, it''s cool; it''s good for me.', 60269, 0), (434966, 'Every night I fell asleep to a different Beatles album. So I''m very familiar with the Beatles Ringo was my favorite Beatle until I grew up and then changed. I made the switch over to George Harrison just in time to regain my cool. ', 69337, 0), (434967, 'Once Johnny Cash and Waylon Jennings are not cool on country radio, it''s time for a new format.', 69338, 0), (434968, 'That point of life when I learned I could cook, that always made me understand what cooks felt like feeding other people. It''s okay to receive, but it''s really cool to give, so food is to me sexy because it''s the fact that someone is giving it to someone else.', 69322, 0), (434969, 'I really had a problem with being ''the man.'' I''m past it now, but that was my insecurity. I ran from that. I was cool with being No. 3 on the call sheet or No. 2.', 69322, 0), (434970, 'Whenever we can, we try to talk to students. If I can, I''ll invite kids from a school to a sound check and take questions from them. I want to show them it''s cool to play the trombone. Kids are influenced by what''s accessible to them. It''s hard for kids to be introduced to music other than what they see on TV and video.', 68252, 0), (434971, 'Whenever I go jamming, people are looking to cut me. The young ones learn my stuff and come play it at me, and I have to learn other stuff. I feel a lot of pressure. But it''s cool. It''s a good pressure.', 68252, 0), (434972, 'My mom used to model when she was younger, before she went to law school, and I think she thought it was pretty cool. I think my parents saw that acting ultimately made me happy, even though it was a rough ride for a little bit.', 68435, 0), (434973, 'When I was 10, 11, 12, 13, 14, I had so many people I looked up to and was so inspired by all these different people. It''s cool to be in that position.', 68435, 0), (434974, 'There is nothing better than a really cool mystery: you don''t know what''s going to happen, so you keep turning those pages or watching that series.', 68435, 0), (434975, 'It''s cool to be a female character who gets to be really strong and tough.', 68435, 0), (434976, 'You remember where you were doing each scene. ''Oh my God, it was so hot that day.'' It''s kind of cool to see a movie that you haven''t seen in a long time and reflect on that stuff.', 68435, 0), (434977, 'I always wanted to be a blonde, and it was really cool to do that for a while.', 68435, 0), (434978, 'The idea of recognising your strengths and using them in as versatile a way as you can is cool to me.', 22945, 0), (434979, 'I thought it''d be cool to start my own university, in a way.', 68254, 0), (434980, 'I''ve been watching ''Walking Dead'' with my son, and there is absolutely nothing in there I find shocking, but it''s cool, and I like it.', 69339, 0), (434981, 'I like ''The Three Musketeers.'' I like those kind of cool things where they were having a robe and a sword.', 69339, 0), (434982, 'Whether you are a consumer, a hardware maker, a software developer or a provider of cool new services, it''s hard to make a move in the American cellphone world without the permission of the companies that own the pipes.', 69340, 0), (434983, 'I wasn''t always the most fashionable, and I would come to school with cauliflower ear and ringworm. I got made fun of a lot. People called me ''Miss Man'' and ''Guns,'' and people directed a lot of karate jokes at me. I wish that I was at school now that MMA and martial arts is cool, but back when I was in school, people associated it with nerdy stuff.', 25405, 0), (434984, 'I have to be out there to sell these fights; it''s not because I really enjoy getting made up and going to work every day. It''s cool, it''s an awesome job, but it''s still a job. I''m doing it because it helps me make a living and not because I''m so extremely vain that I want to see my face everywhere.', 25405, 0), (434985, 'I like the new, cool, swinging Justin Timberlake.', 66649, 0), (434986, 'Our mission for younger people is to do our best to make exercise cool, hip - the thing to do.', 67828, 0), (434987, 'All of my relationships have happened organically with people who are super cool and in my life and it just moved into a relationship zone.', 69341, 0), (434988, 'It is so cool to think that there are two female, Indian actresses on prime-time American network television who are considered attractive and funny and smart.', 69341, 0), (434989, 'I grew up on Loretta Lynn and Dusty Springfield. I remember lying about it it wasn''t cool to listen to country when I was 12. ', 67397, 0), (434990, 'In early high school years, I was pretty chubby, and I spent a lot of time on my computer, before it was cool to have a computer - because there was a time that was true. So that''s where I developed my personality.', 18940, 0), (434991, 'I''m friends with a lot of my exes, but it took time. We didn''t just get into it. I don''t think you can be friends until you''re cool with them dating someone else. That''s when you know.', 18940, 0), (434992, 'Growing up, I really liked ''Star Wars.'' Han Solo would''ve been really cool to meet. But my stuff was real low-brow. I was watching ''Bugs Bunny.''', 23824, 0), (434993, 'I really like women who get emotional about babies and puppies. I''ve met some incredibly cool women who are tough, but the woman you marry should have a really soft side.', 23824, 0), (434994, 'What a contrast, Trump is feisty but flexible. Obama, cool but rigid. But he had no reason to bend. The media already bought into his shtick. His giddy fan base ate up every white-coated lie.', 10679, 0), (434995, 'For the better part of my adult life, I proudly avoided nerd/nimrod/goober status. I was always just cool enough.', 47094, 0), (434996, 'My parents were really, really cool about supporting what I wanted to do at a really young age. I think I was about 10 when I caught the bug. They would drive me down to New York if there were auditions. When I was 12, I did this show on Broadway called ''High Society,'' so we moved to New York for the run of that.', 12145, 0), (434997, 'I feel like you can''t get an audience to like your character if she''s actually cool, but you can if she''s trying to be cool and sometimes fails.', 12145, 0), (434998, 'Competition is great. And as long as it''s friendly and not a malicious thing, then I think it''s cool.', 47095, 0), (434999, 'I''m kind of the model that everyone thought would always be the Guess, ''Sports Illustrated'' girl. Then, when I started to do high fashion stuff... people were like, ''Oh, so we can have a girl with, like, thighs and a butt in a Tom Ford campaign. Cool.''', 60670, 0), (435000, 'Rag & Bone is a big part of my closet. I just really like how their jeans fit; I wear them a lot, and I think they make really cool staple pieces.', 60670, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (435001, 'High school is when I started to get my sense of fashion together. My queen was Candice Swanepoel, who is a friend of mine now, which is kind of funny, but in high school, I was obsessed. I love her street style: she is always in cool boyfriend jeans, boots, and an awesome coat, which is very much like what I wear.', 60670, 0), (435002, 'Cate Blanchett and others, they get this broad range of all these cool people they can play. Some women really do get it all. For me, it is the same thing that happens over and over. I should change that and maybe write my own thing.', 69342, 0), (435003, 'In a movie, that''s the only time when you''re allowed these kind of fantasies to be lived. Being able to look so cool and be able to fight five bad guys and take them down. When can you do that?', 69343, 0), (435004, 'Tech companies approach you to hold something in a picture and then say, ''This is what I want you to write on your Twitter.'' There are people who get away with that and look really cool doing it, but I''m just not one of them.', 45044, 0), (435005, 'My whole family actually, but my parents. I had such a normal and amazing childhood. I''ve been so lucky. My parents are cool and normal. They don''t talk about the business and I still have stuff to do at their house.', 68257, 0), (435006, 'I wouldn''t say I was bullied, but I was definitely a bit of an outcast. It was more the kids thinking I thought I was cool. I started homeschooling in fifth grade, and I was much happier.', 68257, 0), (435007, 'I had such a normal and amazing childhood. I''ve been so lucky. My parents are cool and normal. They don''t talk about the business, and I still have stuff to do at their house.', 68257, 0), (435008, 'I think we all have different moods - a nerd one day and cool the next. I think everyone has an inner geek, and I know I definitely do.', 68257, 0), (435009, 'I like Penny. She''s cool. Yeah, she dates some idiots, but, although, so have I. So yeah, I would be friends with her. We''d have a lot to talk about.', 68257, 0), (435010, 'I didn''t watch much TV as a kid and I don'' t watch it now. I don'' t find anything beautiful or unique to the medium, and the only thing you can do on TV that you can''t do in film is make a continuing story - which is so cool!', 18666, 0), (435011, 'I love Bob Dylan. Who doesn''t? He tapped into some kind of vein and it keeps on keeping on. There''s nobody like him. He''s unique, and just... way out cool.', 18666, 0), (435012, 'I think it''s so cool to be tall. Even when I''m not wearing heels people tell me I''m tall and I always take it as a complement. The good thing is I can always see everybody in the room.', 68355, 0), (435013, 'I got into the whole Ayurvedic thing. It was really cool.', 67023, 0), (435014, 'It''s not really cool to be singled out.', 67023, 0), (435015, 'I''ve never been cool and I don''t really care about being cool. It''s just an awful lot of time and hair gel wasted.', 25529, 0), (435016, 'I don''t mind not being cool.', 25529, 0), (435017, 'We aren''t cool and never will be.', 25529, 0), (435018, 'Being voted the world''s sexiest vegetarian is about as cool as it gets. It''s not quite as cool as Brad Pitt, but it''ll do.', 25529, 0), (435019, 'There are a lot of movies about misfits that are quite cool, that kind of glamorize it on some level. I think there are fewer films, certainly with a lady at the center, about the agony of what it''s like to feel like you''re not accepted, and you''re different, and somehow you''re weird.', 68436, 0), (435020, 'Icy and earthy, Helen Mirren is a rare, regal presence in a movie age that values the plebeian over the patrician and mass over class. Lauded with an Oscar and an Emmy for playing both Queen Elizabeths, Mirren has matched her cool aristocracy with a boldness of performance and display.', 67854, 0), (435021, 'In the movies, every crazy old fart needs a cool old car. Jack Nicholson drove a spiffy yellow 1970 Dodge Challenger two-door in ''The Bucket List.'' In ''Gran Torino,'' the cranky pensioner played by Clint Eastwood not only owned a 1972 GT Sport, he also used to build cars like that at the Ford plant.', 67854, 0), (435022, 'I love being not cool.', 8055, 0), (435023, 'I don''t feel like songs should be hoarded. I don''t feel like one''s tainted if somebody else does it. That''s the mark of artistry - take a song that''s maybe even a really popular song and do it your own way. I think that''s cool.', 66588, 0), (435024, 'When you''re writing with an artist or for an artist, you have to help them serve their vision. That''s the cool part about writing songs. There are no rules.', 66588, 0), (435025, 'If I''m the biggest artist in the world, cool, but I want to just be me.', 68174, 0), (435026, 'I try to look cool. I strategize. Sometimes it''s like - that''s part of the strategizing, to make it seem like I don''t think about it.', 68174, 0), (435027, 'I really liked the snake that breaks out of the cage in the beginning of the movie. I saw it in real life, and it was really cool. Really big and fat. The owls are cool as well, but you can''t really pet them.', 60164, 0), (435028, 'Draco''s not really a bully. He''s not exactly the biggest, strongest guy in the world. He''s more a rich, snobby person. He thinks of himself as really cool.', 60164, 0), (435029, 'I would miss months of school and then return with bright blond hair. Needless to say, there was bullying. I wasn''t beaten up daily, but there was name-calling and jealousy. You have to bear in mind that ''Harry Potter'' wasn''t cool. I wasn''t part of the ''Terminator'' franchise.', 60164, 0), (435030, 'I started on the clarinet. I was going to a music school - my mother took me - and the guy said, ''What do you want to play?'' I said the drums, and my mother said, ''No, you don''t. You don''t want to play the drums.'' So I said, ''Maybe the trumpet would be cool.'' And my mother said, ''I don''t think so.'' And then the clarinet was handed to me.', 69344, 0), (435031, 'My wife is cool enough to let me write about personal things, to be a songwriter exploring the shadowy sides of love.', 69345, 0), (435032, 'My friends in Paris are writers, or something like that, whereas my friends in New York are doing cool stuff in finance and living very different lives. In writing, it''s pretty solitary, so it doesn''t really matter who''s around.', 69346, 0), (435033, 'Houston is kind of a melting pot. There are many different cultures and ethnicities represented out there, even on my team. It''s really cool: you''ll see so many different things.', 69347, 0), (435034, 'Obviously, you get to do a lot of great things and cool opportunities at the Super Bowl. But at the end of the day, we all want to be here as a player. That''s the goal, and that''s why I work so dang hard.', 69347, 0), (435035, 'Growing up, you''d see Michael Jordan on everything from Gatorade to shoes - everything. Obviously, that''s something pretty cool for an athlete to aspire to.', 69347, 0), (435036, 'The one thing I know is, if I play good ball, things have tended to come along with it. Everything that I''ve ever done in my career has come off of playing good football. And so I realize I need to go out there, and I need to take care of my business; then everything else - all these cool, great things - come along with it.', 69347, 0), (435037, 'People always ask, ''Man, why don''t you come out and enjoy it? Why don''t you celebrate? Why don''t you have any fun?'' My fun is Sundays. Anybody can go to the club. You don''t have to be good at going to the club to go to the club. You have to be good to be playing on Sundays, and to me, that''s what''s cool.', 69347, 0), (435038, 'It makes no difference to my family where one comes from as long as we make each other happy. They are pretty cool like that.', 69348, 0), (435039, 'I''m not really as cool and collected as ''Mrs. Funnybones'', but she is the woman I want to be.', 38710, 0), (435040, 'I want to be somebody, a person, first that people remember, but also, I want music that I release to still be around. I don''t want it to just be cool for a second and be gone.', 67360, 0), (435041, 'Being a big Braves fan, Turner Field would be cool to play a show at.', 67360, 0), (435042, 'Getting hit is not cool.', 69349, 0), (435043, 'The problem to me is violence. It''s not cool to kill somebody or hurt people.', 67788, 0), (435044, 'It''s cool when your husband starts to sing some old Merle Haggard song and I can pop in with a harmony and it doesn''t sound too bad.', 56, 0), (435045, 'I wanted to be Cher for a long time, but not for the singing. I just thought she was so cool. I wanted her long hair, and I wanted to weigh five pounds.', 56, 0), (435046, 'What we do every night is we change out the set list as much as we can to make sure that (fans can) go home and tell their friends they experienced something unique and cool.', 69350, 0), (435047, 'It''s all these young country bucks doing Skynyrd songs, which is pretty cool to us.', 67029, 0), (435048, 'Goteborg used to be a not very cool place to live. The culture centered around shrimp and bingo. Bands played Copenhagen and Stockholm and skipped Goteborg.', 68440, 0), (435049, 'Can anything be less cool than defending the motion picture academy?', 8777, 0), (435050, 'Redford always has been a cool presence both before and behind the camera. His best movie as a filmmaker, 1994''s ''Quiz Show,'' exhibits a classicism verging on self-repression, and the social indignation in many of his films engages more than moves you.', 8777, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (435051, 'J. G. Ballard is just an example of the writers I like. Philip K. Dick is obviously one of them. I''m a big fan of William Gibson as well. He started cyberpunk with ''Neuromancer.'' I''ve come to know him a little bit over Twitter, of all places, and I was always a huge fan of his. It''s very cool to know he even knows I exist.', 68439, 0), (435052, 'My dad put me with all the greatest people. It definitely helped me now, because I know so much more about music and composition. It''s cool. I love Pops. I''m super thankful for everything he''s done to help my career.', 68262, 0), (435053, 'When we dropped ''Toot It And Boot It,'' Mustard didn''t even do beats, and now he''s killin'' it. So it''s just cool to see all of my bros taking over.', 68262, 0), (435054, 'Metal has its own code of cool, but it''s not really trying to be cool. And that was very refreshing to me, that metal is very much about expressing something that seems awesome to you even if, at the time, much of the world was going to mock and reject it.', 16432, 0), (435055, 'You get this really cool groove when you''re playing just piano, bass, and drums where everyone''s sort of feeling each other''s space, which is the only way to put it, but it really is true, and everyone''s sort of sitting in their own pocket. It''s kind of jazz-like.', 16432, 0), (435056, 'I remember going with my mom to a random garage sale as a kid and thinking what a cool treasure hunt that whole world was. Only to transition as an adult to think, ''What a gross place that really is.''', 67411, 0), (435057, 'Check-ins are cool, but kind of a pain.', 68927, 0), (435058, 'Many founders hire just because it seems like a cool thing to do, and people always ask how many employees you have.', 68927, 0), (435059, 'In rock and roll, homosexuality was accepted, but it was less cool to say it.', 57404, 0), (435060, 'Growing up, it was uncool to admit that your family had any money. And then, instantly, money was cool. In Reagan''s parlance, it was about freedom of the individual, which was freedom to be greedy... individual versus society. There was a weird seduction in that, which I still feel.', 57404, 0), (435061, 'It''s cool when frat boys say, ''Yeah, ''Hedwig!'' I''d like to see that same thing happen with ''Shortbus.''', 57404, 0), (435062, 'My mom was a little weepy. My dad was very logical about it. Once they realized you can''t change, they wanted to know that you can be happy and be gay. Once they realized that, they were very cool about it.', 57404, 0), (435063, 'Public relations and marketing are something companies do to move product. It is not meaningful. It is not cool. Yet because it is cheap, easy, and lucrative to cover, blogs want to convince you that it is.', 14605, 0), (435064, 'Lupe Fiasco is kinda cool. I like him a lot.', 69351, 0), (435065, 'I''ve never done anything because I thought it would look cool.', 861, 0), (435066, 'You don''t have to carry a designer bag that costs more than a car to look cool.', 68388, 0), (435067, 'There are lots of really interesting little planets out there in the Kuiper Belt, but Pluto''s the only one that''s got all the cool attributes.', 66716, 0), (435068, 'I like the planets because they are real places that you can go to and send machines to. Faraway astronomy - galactic astronomy and extra-galactic astronomy - is really cool stuff, but to me, it''s about destinations.', 66716, 0), (435069, 'I just worry about myself. I''m just gonna be me and do me. If people appreciate it, cool. If not, I''m gonna still be me.', 69352, 0), (435070, 'I''ve always been into guitars... we want to put keyboards on, but keyboard players don''t look cool onstage, they just keep their heads down. There has never been a cool keyboard player, apart from Elton John.', 13014, 0), (435071, 'Every year, tens of millions of salmon return to the pristine shores of Bristol Bay in Alaska. They linger in the bay''s cool, shallow waters before charging up nearby streams to spawn and create another generation of wild salmon.', 67862, 0), (435072, 'The cool thing about my show and me is that I''m a writer, and I''m a writer first if I don''t have music.', 60183, 0), (435073, 'You get a timeless cool card in New York.', 68102, 0), (435074, 'I don''t know who came up with this idea that it''s cool to hate on other girls, ''cause it''s not.', 68220, 0), (435075, 'I think the Mama people remember is from ''Mama''s Family.'' She really turned into a pretty cool character. The sketches from the ''Burnett'' show, if people are old enough to remember, were written by writers who all hated their mothers.', 58173, 0), (435076, 'I love the Army-Navy surplus store Surplus Value Center. They have really good long underwear and multicolored bandanas, cool camo jackets, and really, really scary-looking knives. If you''re into that sort of thing.', 69353, 0), (435077, 'Morgan Freeman is so class. He''s so cool. He''s so scary.', 14367, 0), (435078, 'I may just keep releasing singles ''til I run out of music, which is kind of cool in a way - as long as people don''t go, ''Oh my God, not another one!''', 69354, 0), (435079, 'Tobey''s a mellow, cool guy. He''s just a good guy. I know that''s not the answer you want, and I don''t mean that as the political thing to say, but he''s a nice guy.', 36406, 0), (435080, 'I don''t think it''s cool for people to say, ''You shouldn''t reference God because I don''t believe that, and I don''t want to hear it.'' Well, there''s a lot of stuff I don''t believe that I still gotta hear.', 385, 0), (435081, 'I follow all these fashion blogs that are cool and inspire me. I''m not really obsessed with anyone except for the people that I like romantically. I get excited when they post. Sometimes I like to stalk my exes.', 66658, 0), (435082, 'My mother was so stylish, but she never pushed that on me. She always thought I looked cool.', 67056, 0), (435083, 'I went to Catholic high school for half a year and religion wasn''t the cool thing to talk about even at a catholic high school. It never came up.', 67484, 0), (435084, 'I''ve always loved the mixture of crushing live drums with a programmed groove, that really cool blend, like in the verse there''s a really funky drum beat that is programmed then it comes in to the chorus; you''ve got that enormous human feel where the band kicks in.', 11490, 0), (435085, 'Some girls are intimidated by my height, obviously. But a lot of girls do like it, so that''s cool.', 69355, 0), (435086, 'I tried to be a goth for a while. I''d pour baby powder on my face and paint my lips black, but that didn''t last long. I thought I looked cool at the time. But then you look back and wonder, ''Why did anyone let me out of the house looking like that?''', 69356, 0), (435087, 'People don''t know exactly what I do they just know I''m ''cool.'' ', 69233, 0), (435088, 'Klaus from the Teddybears, Bloodshy and Avant and Mike Snow, they''ve done lots of Britney Spears production. They went backwards from production to being in a band, which might be cool. I might do that, too, one day.', 69233, 0), (435089, 'I appreciate people who are authentic. Someone who just wants to be cool, I can tell when their intentions aren''t right.', 69233, 0), (435090, 'Selling MP3s or physical copies, it''s still cool, but I think it''s slowly becoming outdated to where people just want to build a culture.', 69233, 0), (435091, 'Gucci is a rapper that doesn''t try and be anything he''s not - he''s straight up. Yeah, maybe it''s ironic and all, but I''m just a fan and have been one since day one. Gucci Mane is the cool uncle I never had, even though I''m sure I''m probably older than him.', 69233, 0), (435092, 'There aren''t many poster children for cool angst. Everybody thinks it''s cool if you''re the bad girl.', 15776, 0), (435093, 'I think you go through a period as a teenager of being quite cool and unaffected by things.', 68452, 0), (435094, 'I think sometimes I guess you see records, say you want to get there and use that as motivation. In a way, it''s kind of cool if there is a possibility to rewrite history and be up there with the greats of Olympic history.', 30837, 0), (435095, 'I''ve really enjoyed working together with Apple to help launch their new streaming service. It is really cool to see Apple getting involved.', 69357, 0), (435096, 'Personally, I was never the cool kid. I was always sort of a bookworm.', 68410, 0), (435097, 'Spider-Man''s probably my favorite. You see, Batman is a billionaire and there''s nothing really cool about a billionaire saving the world. But Spider-Man is Peter Parker, a conflicted character who puts on a suit and saves the world. I love that.', 68410, 0), (435098, 'I''d love to be an artist that''s multifaceted. At the moment, I am not. But wouldn''t that be cool if I was like, ''Yeah, let me pull out my guitar and play you a song.'' I would adore that. I am so far not gifted in that way. But I am a very hard worker and a very determined person, so who knows?', 67062, 0), (435099, 'I went to a high school that didn''t have many people in it. There were, like, 60 people in my senior class. There was a group of cool kids and a group of really dorky kids, and I was probably the coolest of the really dorky kids.', 68455, 0), (435100, 'Every time I take a photo, it goes into SnapSeed. Even if it''s just a price tag on something, it still goes into SnapSeed, and I start editing it. I''m not a photographer, so I need all the help I can get when it comes to make a picture look cool.', 48278, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (435101, 'Basically, after an ABC sitcom I did, I ended up with a holding deal with 20th Century Fox. Absolutely cool. It pays you to be unemployed. And the bigger the entity that gives you the deal, the better.', 10154, 0), (435102, 'Most of the time you''re too busy to think about it. But every now and then you say, ''I work at ''Saturday Night Live,'' and that is so cool.', 1219, 0), (435103, 'When I was younger I did karate and martial arts, and I think it''s really cool for girls to have those kinds of abilities.', 67065, 0), (435104, 'You can''t be a strong or cool woman and be represented except in a harsh way, looking mean and cold and hard. It''s like reverse sexism.', 13347, 0), (435105, 'I live a very nice life. I have a wonderful time. But it''s not lived drawing on a full level. I''m relaxed, cool, and enjoying it.', 22775, 0), (435106, 'I think it''s most important to, rather than just do what everybody else is doing, like tons of selfies, find out what makes you excited. You know, is it taking pictures and doing cool makeup and making yourself look great? If so, wonderful. Is it music? Is it teaching something? Are you great at teaching?', 22683, 0), (435107, 'I''m afraid one thing - I don''t like heights. Heights bug me out. I''m not cool with heights. I refuse to do a comedy show 12 stories up. I''m fearless about everything else.', 67383, 0), (435108, 'In recording, you''re trying to make something work sonically - getting the right inflection on the right guitar sound - and maybe a part that would be musically great doesn''t sound as cool. On paper, though, it''s all stripped back. The musical idea is the one that wins.', 9972, 0), (435109, 'People see my photos and think I labor over my image and I''m this cool, brooding artist. But I''m just having fun with it.', 68285, 0), (435110, 'For the last few years, it''s been so chic for everybody to be miserable. Like if you''re in with the cool